title: barbecued wieners and sauerkraut
directions: Make the barbecue sauce by cooking the diced onion in oil until lightly browned.
Add ketchup, water, brown sugar and dry mustard; simmer 15 minutes.
Drain sauerkraut and spread out in a shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top this with the frankfurters and spoon the barbecue sauce over them.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: my lasagne
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in saucepan.
Brown onion and garlic in the oil.
Add the hamburger and the salt and pepper; brown and add to sauce.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Layer in long pan: 1/3 sauce, 1/2 lasagne, 1/2 Ricotta, 1/2 Mozzarella and 1/3 Parmesan.
Repeat with sauce and Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Remove any excess fat from chicken quarters. Cover chicken with water and boil approximately 20-30 minutes or until done. (Do not over cook or meat will become stringy.) Remove chicken from pot and cool; remove skin and debone; set aside. Add cream of chicken soup to chicken broth and stir.

title: cookies in a hurry
directions: Add raisins, nuts, chocolate chips, etc.
Drop by rounded spoonful and bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup and water.
Shape into balls and brown.
Pour off grease.
Add soup and water.

title: no bake "fudge"
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine over low heat.
In bowl, combine nuts and graham cracker crumbs.
Add sweetened condensed milk and vanilla; stir until well mixed.
Add chocolate mixture and mix well.
Pat mixture into a well-greased 12 x 8-inch pan. Refrigerate until cool; cut into squares.
(Best if kept cold until eaten.)

title: cucumber-broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up ingredients.
Put in bowl.
Add dressing.
Cover and marinate for 12 hours or overnight.
Serve.

title: mama's sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight. Yield: 2 1/2 cups.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix in bowl.
Add season salt to taste.

title: savory chicken stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions but do not let stand as directed on package. In 12 x 8-inch baking dish spoon stuffing down center of dish, leaving space on sides of stuffing to arrange chicken.
Arrange chicken pieces around stuffing, overlapping if necessary.
In bowl combine soup, milk and parsley.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil; bake 15 minutes.
Uncover; bake 10 minutes more or until chicken is done.
Garnish with paprika and watercress if desired.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve sugar into water; add frozen juices and pineapple juice.
Mix well.
About 10 minutes before serving, add cold ginger ale and club soda.
Can add food coloring for color scheme. Add a fifth of vodka, if desired.
Yields 32 (6-ounce) servings.

title: blackberry parfait
directions: Set aside some berries for decoration.
Use the rest to make a sauce.
Add the sugar. Whip the cream.
Blend the egg yolks and the berry mixture into the cream. Freeze.
(Can also use strawberries or raspberries.)

title: quick beef and broccoli
directions: Slice steak diagonally across grain into thin strips; place in a shallow dish.
Combine soy sauce, dry sherry, cornstarch and sugar.
Pour over flank steak and set aside.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl melt butter and sugar; microwave until chips are melted, 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir until mixture is well blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.
These taste like Reese's peanut butter cups.

title: beef marengo
directions: Trim excess fat from roast.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Brown in hot oil in a large Dutch oven.
Remove meat.
Add onion, celery and garlic to pan drippings; saute until tender.
Add meat, 1/2 cup wine and next 7 ingredients to mixture; bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
Discard bay leaves.

title: barb's dip
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with chips or vegetable sticks.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles; drain and allow to cool. In a skillet, melt margarine.
Saute onion and green bell pepper until tender.
Add meat and brown slowly; set aside.
In a small bowl, stir together tomato paste, sour cream, sugar and salt and set aside.
In a large bowl, toss together noodles and cottage cheese.
Layer 1/2 noodle and cottage cheese mixture into a casserole dish.
Spread with tomato sour cream mixture, then layer 1/2 meat mixture.
Layer remaining noodle mixture, then meat. Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut rounder patties
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Cook for 1 hour over very low heat; then add vanilla, butter and food coloring until color desired.
Beat until creamy and spoon out on waxed paper to make patties.

title: south carolina corn fritters
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, shortening and milk.
Stir in the corn.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot shortening.
Fry for 3 to 5 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6.

title: salsa verde
directions: Grind all ingredients, except oil and vinegar, in a meat grinder; mix well.
Add oil and vinegar; mix well.
Pour into gallon jugs.
Refrigerate for 3 days before serving.
Very hot.

title: crabmeat cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl, except margarine and cracker crumbs.
Shape into cakes.
Dip in crumbs.
Fry.

title: veggie bars
directions: Pinch together crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown (12 to 15 minutes).
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese, mayo and Ranch dressing to taste.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Add vegetables, then Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate, then cut into squares.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Put in greased and floured loaf pan and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: creole okra
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in bacon drippings in Dutch oven until onion is tender.
Add next 4 ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in file powder.
Serve over hot rice.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a skillet, combine ground beef, onions and bell pepper.
Cook until beef is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain well.
Stir in pizza sauce and soup. Pour meat mixture over noodles evenly.
Top with Mozzarella. Arrange pepperoni slices over casserole. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Melt margarine with chocolate.
Beat eggs; add sugar and beat until foaming, then add chocolate mixture.
Add flour, salt and pecans.
Last, add vanilla.
Put in greased and floured pan, 8 x 16-inch size.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix asparagus, peas, drained mushrooms with soup.
Spread in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice in boiler.
Add margarine and pineapple.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cook sweet potatoes (about 6), sliced lengthwise. Pour cooked mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a casserole dish.

title: fettuccine alfredo "light"
directions: Prepare fettuccine.
To cooked, drained pasta, add margarine, cheese and skimmed milk.
Toss to mix.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 (1-cup) servings.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Crush crackers into crumbs.
Mix with oleo.
Make a crust in 9 x 13-inch pan (save a few crumbs for later).
In mixing bowl combine puddings and milk; blend well, then add ice cream.
Should be soft, but not soupy.
Blend well with pudding, then pour over crust.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with remaining crumbs. Cover and refrigerate.

title: italian macaroni salad
directions: *Radishes may be substituted for olives.

title: middle eastern candy(fudge)
directions: Dissolve the sugar in water and cook in a saucepan until it forms a thick syrup.
Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Gradually add the powdered milk, stirring constantly.
Return to heat (very low burner) and stir for about 2 minutes.
Add rose water.
Stir (batter is thick).

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Bake 1 layer of Jiffy Mix white cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or the Duncan Hines cake mix in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans for 10 to 15 minutes.
Be sure to thoroughly grease and flour pans.
Cool the cake.

title: festive fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until it reaches a rolling boil. Boil and stir 5 minutes more, then take off heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until completely melted; then stir in the cut-up nuts and vanilla.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool. Cut into 30 pieces.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and eggs.
Mix until blended.
Add soda to applesauce.
Blend all dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture.
Then add your applesauce.
Fold in raisins and nuts. Pour into tube pan (well greased and floured).
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemoned carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water with bouillon cube until tender, but not mushy. Drain carrots and set aside. In a pan, melt butter. Add parsley, green onion, lemon juice and rind and pepper. Mix well. Add carrots and serve hot.

title: plum surprise cake
directions: Mix the cooking oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add plums, red food coloring, flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add cinnamon, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend and then whip.

title: easy corn dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together and refrigerate for several hours. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, eggs and flour.
Add chocolate chips and chopped pecans.
Pour into deep dish pie shell that has been slightly cooked in oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: fudge marble pound cake
directions: Mix well with mixer.
Reserve 1 cup of batter to mix with chocolate packet in mix.
Pour the rest in a floured and greased Bundt pan.
Pour the mixed chocolate packet and batter around the top of the cake; use a knife to spread the chocolate mixture through the cake.
Bake for 1 hour until firm or longer if necessary.

title: instant nonfat milk
directions: Put water, dry milk powder and ice cubes into blender container.
Cover blender.
Press button 8 for 10 seconds.
Drink immediately or store in refrigerator.
Yield:
1 cup to 1 quart.

title: bride's delight
directions: Let set covered for 24 hours.

title: deb's date balls
directions: Mix margarine, dates, vanilla and sugar in saucepan and cook on low heat for 5 minutes.
Add egg and cook 5 minutes longer, until dates are all mixed.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Let cool and roll into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef and onion. In a casserole dish, crunch up tortilla chips. Mix in pan with meat the can of beans, soup, picante and 3 slices of cheese. Heat until hot, but do not "cook." Spoon mixture onto chips and stir, trying to get some of the sauce on the bottom of chips. Sprinkle bag of cheese on top. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until cheese is bubbling.

title: spicy barbecue spareribs
directions: Put spareribs in shallow roasting pan and roast in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients and simmer in small pot for 15 minutes.
Brush mixture on spareribs frequently and roast for another 1/2 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies with cake mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork which has been dipped in water. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll into a sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Butter a Bundt pan well.
Place chopped pecans in bottom and build up with biscuits.
Melt the margarine and brown sugar over low heat.
Pour evenly over biscuits and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pan by turning over onto large plate, letting caramel drizzle over sides.

title: vegetables and pasta nests
directions: In separate pans, cook vegetables and pasta according to package directions and drain.
Melt margarine in saucepan and stir in flour, lemon peel, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add yogurt and vegetables; heat almost to boiling.
Spoon half of the vegetable sauce mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: slush
directions: Put into a large container; mix well and freeze.
Stir several times while freezing.
(Takes a couple of days to freeze.)

title: melts in your mouth dessert
directions: Mix flour, melted oleo and nuts into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down evenly to cover entire pan bottom.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip and spread on top of baked crust.
Make up 2 packages pudding according to directions and pour over cream cheese mixture layer.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.

title: cinnamon syrup
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Beat with a whisk.
Serve warm over French toast.

title: eggplant manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel eggplant and slice into 12 pieces, 1/4-inch thick.
Slice from top to bottom.
Lay slices on a paper towel and sprinkle salt on them to allow water to drain from slices.
In skillet, cook eggplant with olive oil.
Drain on paper towel.
Roll 1 1/2 ounces Ricotta cheese on each slice.
Pour tomato sauce in casserole dish and neatly place manicotti in rows on top of sauce.
Bake at 400° until hot.
Remove manicotti from pan to serving dish.

title: grandma's gingerbread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake in a very slow oven at 300° for 1 hour or until cake tester inserted in center comes clean.
Serve warm and, if desired, with whipped cream or applesauce.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Peel and boil onion and potatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Add soup to water with potatoes and onions.
When cheese soup is melted, add asparagus.
I also put in a shredded carrot for color. In a small pan, melt oleo.
Add flour until smooth.
Add to boiling soup to thicken.
Remove from heat and put in evaporated milk.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Grease pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes or more.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze all water out.
Drain water chestnuts and chop finely.
Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Delicious with crackers.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue made from the 3 egg whites.
Bake to brown at 375°.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and saute pork until lightly brown on all sides (about 5 to 6 minutes).
Place in baking pan. In a small saucepan, combine jelly, vermouth and mustard.
Cook over medium heat until smooth, stirring constantly.
Pour 3/4 of mixture over pork.
(I save a little for serving purposes.)
Bake in
preheated 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Baste every 15 minutes.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch slices and spoon sauce over meat.

title: taco dip supreme
directions: Spread bean dip on large round or oblong pan.
Smash avocados and whip with sugar and spread over beans.
Mix envelope of taco seasoning in container of sour cream and spread.
Take sliced black olives, cut up green onions and cut up tomatoes and place all over, then last sprinkle cheese all over.
All you need is tortilla chips now to dunk!

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together cornmeal, sour cream, corn, oil, onion and eggs. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Put the remaining ingredients into a colander; let drain well. Pour the sauce mixture over the vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate overnight or a day ahead of time.
This will keep for a week in the refrigerator.

title: sticky pecan rolls
directions: The night before, spread pecans on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan. Place dinner rolls on top of pecans.
Drizzle margarine over rolls. Sprinkle instant pudding over rolls.
Spread brown sugar over pudding.
Cover with Saran Wrap and leave to rise overnight.
To bake, remove Saran Wrap and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: beef burgundy
directions: In skillet (or Dutch oven), brown meat in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Serve over noodles.

title: skillet supper
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add salt and pepper, chili powder and tomatoes.
Let simmer for a few minutes.
Add noodles and sour cream.
Simmer on low for about 15 minutes.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Mix sugar, walnuts and cinnamon; set aside.
Spoon about 1 teaspoon butter into each of the 10 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups. Spoon sugar mixture evenly into cups.
Top with a biscuit.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden. Invert from pan immediately.

title: magnolia room's fruit salad
directions: Whip cream cheese in a mixer.
Add powdered sugar and mix until well blended.
Add vanilla and blend in salad dressing or mayonnaise.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Remove seeds from peppers (wear gloves when doing this).
Put peppers in blender; process until fine.
Add enough water to make 3 1/2 cups pulp.
Bring to boil and add 1 package pectin.
Add the sugar and bring to boil again.
Boil four minutes.
Put in jars. Color changes as it cooks, but will return to normal when it cools.
Serve with cream cheese and crackers.

title: dietetic banana nugget cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients with the exception of oats.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop mixture in small balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for about 12 minutes.
Dough is soft.
Keeps better if refrigerated.

title: applesauce snacking cake
directions: In medium bowl mix applesauce, bran, Egg Beaters and molasses. Let stand 5 minutes.
In small bowl, blend flour, baking soda and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat sugar and margarine until creamy.
Beat in bran mixture until smooth.
Blend in flour mixture; stir in raisins.
Spread batter in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into 48 bars.
Contains 60 calories, 2 g fat.

title: barbecue meatballs #1
directions: Mix ingredients and form balls.

title: lima beans
directions: Cook beans until tender and drain.
Mix everything together. Sprinkle cheese as topping.
Crumble bacon on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese pizza puffs
directions: Lightly coat a cookie sheet with Pam spray; set aside. Separate dough into 10 pieces.
Make an indentation in center of each with your thumb.
Lightly sprinkle each indentation with oregano and garlic powder.
Top each with a cheese cube.
Pull dough over the cheese and firmly pinch dough together so cheese is completely enclosed.
(Very important to prevent cheese from oozing out during baking.)
Place on prepared cookie sheet, seam-side down.
Place puffs 2 inches apart; lightly brush tops with pizza sauce.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until golden.
Yield:
10 puffs.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage until crumbly; drain.
Add remaining ingredients in crock-pot or skillet.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted.

title: casserole chicken
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into 3-quart, ungreased casserole. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut apples, bananas and oranges into small pieces.
Put in mixing bowl.
Drain water off raisins and add to other ingredients.
Stir in mayonnaise and mix lightly.
Can be served in bowl or on lettuce leaves.
Serves 6.

title: tacos verde, blanco, y rojo(green, white and red tacos)
directions: Cook onion in the 1 tablespoon oil until tender; stir in tomato sauce, peppers and salt.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken or pork; heat thoroughly.
Keep warm.
In small skillet, heat the 2 tablespoons oil.
Holding tortillas with tongs, dip each tortilla in the hot oil for about 10 seconds or just until limp. Drain on paper toweling.

title: punch bowl cake(serves 20)
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Cut into small squares.
Layer 1/3 of cake into bottom of punch bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix milk and instant pudding.
Pour 1/3 over cake.
On top of that put 1 container Cool Whip.
Sprinkle 1/3 of Heath bits over that.
Repeat with 2 more layers of cake, pudding, Cool Whip and Heath bits.

title: fruity lite jello
directions: Boil 2 cups water, empty 2 boxes of jello in water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add the pineapple and liquid plus 1 cup cold water. Refrigerate until jello sets.
Remove from refrigerator and add Dream Whip topping, prepared as directed.
Using electric mixer fold in topping until well mixed.

title: cherry delight
directions: Crush graham crackers in gallon plastic bag, add granulated sugar.
Shake until well mixed.
Place in a 9x9 baking dish.
Melt butter and pour over graham crackers.
Mix butter and crackers until well coated.
Pat lightly in bottom of dish.
Combine cream cheese, milk, and powdered sugar. Beat until creamy.
Spread over graham crackers.
Sprinkle nuts between layers of cream cheese and Dream Whip.
Blend Dream Whip according to package directions. Spread over cream cheese.
Put cherry pie filling over whipped cream layer.
Store in refrigerator.
(You
may use blueberry pie filling instead of cherry.)

title: bakeless cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo in saucepan.
Heat and boil hard for one minute, then remove.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in flour.
Blend in syrup.
Cook on greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: silver sweet quiche
directions: Line pie or quiche dish with pastry.
Cook white sweet corn according to package directions; drain.
Place in bottom of pastry. Sprinkle cheese over corn.
Beat eggs, cream, onion and seasonings together and pour over corn-cheese mixture.
Sprinkle bacon over top.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight. Makes very large amount.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all dry ingredients in a big Ziploc bag.
Shake potatoes in bag and place in pan of melted margarine.
Pour remaining dry ingredients from Ziploc over potatoes.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Do not turn potatoes while cooking.

title: mixed vegetables mornay
directions: Cook vegetables.
Drain.
Melt butter.	Blend in flour. Do not brown.
Add milk and cook
over
low flame until thickened, stirring constantly. Add
seasonings and cheeses.
Place vegetables	in
casserole and cover
with
sauce.
Toss
bread cubes in melted butter and top
casserole.	Bake at 425° until cubes are lightly browned.

title: pork chop and stuffing casserole
directions: Lightly brown chops in lard or drippings in large glass-ceramic skillet. Remove chops from skillet and sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cook onion in drippings in a skillet 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in stuffing mix and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt. Combine soup with water. Add chopped apple, zucchini and diluted soup to stuffing mixture, stirring lightly to combine. Place in a large glass-ceramic open roaster. Place pork chops on top of stuffing. Cover pan tightly with foil. Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 45 minutes or until chops are done. Yield: 6 servings.

title: glace nuts
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in pan.
Cover and cook on medium heat without stirring until it comes to a boil. Uncover and boil until 300° (hard crack stage).
Meanwhile, spread nuts in shallow pan and put in oven heated to 350° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat under candy mix to very low and add heated nuts, butter and flavorings.
Stir just until nuts are coated and butter is melted.
Turn into large sieve or colander and let set one minute to drain off extra syrup.
Spread onto 2 buttered cookie sheets and separate quickly with 2 forks.
When cool, pack in containers.

title: wassail bowl
directions: In a large kettle combine cider, sugar and juices.
Tie spices in a white bag.
Add to cider and nutmeg.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove spice bag. Serve hot with a cinnamon stick, used to stir the drink in a teacup.

title: beignet
directions: Mix yeast with warm water; stir well.
Add 2 cups flour, salt, sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Add 2 more cups flour.
Mix well and then turn out on floured bag (a plastic bag works well), and knead, knead, knead, then place in large bowl with just a little oil.
Spread in bowl, cover and allow to rise.

title: italian beef
directions: Mix all together and pour over roast.
Place in crock-pot.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream well the oleo and sugar.
Mix eggs, flour, baking powder, soda, cocoa and salt together with water, vanilla and kraut.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 2 layer or sheet cake pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in salted water; drain and cool.
Add to mixture of vinegar, sugar and tomato soup.
Add onions, green pepper, oil, mustard and Worcestershire.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for at least 12 hours.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and tomatoes.
Simmer all together for 15 minutes. Add baked beans.
Mix together and put into baking dish.
Mix corn muffin mix according to directions on box.
Put over top of bean mixture and bake according to muffin mix recipe.
If multiplying this recipe, cut down on chili powder.

title: frozen key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 9-inch pie plate, with fork, stir cracker crumbs, butter and sugar until moistened.
With hand, press mixture onto bottom and up sides of pie plate.
Bake crust 10 minutes.
Cool completely in pie plate on wire rack.

title: delicious gooey brownies
directions: In a
bowl, mix all the ingredients (melt chocolate and butter in double boiler first).
Put in pan (mixture should be about 1/2 inch thick) and put into 350° preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Fork will be slightly gooey upon testing, not completely dry.

title: holiday magic yams
directions: Drain peaches; reserve juice.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup peach juice; set aside.
In skillet, heat remaining peach juice, brown sugar, cranberry sauce, cinnamon, nutmeg and butter.
When butter is melted, add cornstarch mixture.
Stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Place yams and peaches (sliced) in casserole dish.
Add liquid mixture.
Heat for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: In a 13x9 inch baking dish, layer refried beans, bean dip and onion.
Sprinkle avocado with lemon juice and arrange on bean layer.
Stir together sour cream and mayonnaise and carefully spread on avocados.
Sprinkle taco seasoning mix, then Monterey Jack cheese, cheddar cheese and olives.
Arrange tomatoes and green onion on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix up all ingredients and pour in dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes with cover on.
Stir once.

title: creamy tuna rice casserole
directions: Put rice, milk and seasoning in double boiler.
Cook over boiling water until tender (40 minutes).
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well; put in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: better vegetable stew
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Cover two baking sheets with aluminum foil, and drizzle with olive oil. Arrange potatoes, carrots and onions on one baking sheet. Drizzle with more olive oil and sprinkle with oregano, cumin and mustard seeds. Place the garlic bulb on the baking sheet. Arrange the peppers and tomatoes on the second baking sheet, and sprinkle with olive oil. Place both pans in the oven. Cook, stirring the contents occasionally, until the potatoes, carrots and onions are tender and the peppers and tomatoes are black, about 30 to 45 minutes. The bell peppers and tomatoes may take a little longer to cook than the potatoes, carrots, onions, and garlic. Feel free to remove the baking sheet of potatoes earlier than the baking sheet of bell peppers. Reduce the oven's heat to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Transfer the tomatoes and peppers into a medium size mixing bowl with the canned tomatoes and cinnamon stick. Cover the bowl, and let it set for 30 minutes.

Skin and seed the peppers and skin the tomatoes. Chop the peppers and tomatoes and place them into a medium size pot that can be placed in the oven. Squeeze the garlic from skins into the pot and stir in the potato mixture and chickpeas. Season with lemon juice, salt, and black pepper. Cover the stew, and bake it for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread ingredients in layers: pineapple, blueberries, half of the sugar, to be sprinkled over the berries, dry cake mix, melted margarine and chopped nuts. Sprinkle last half of the sugar over nuts.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: twinkie cake lite
directions: Cut Twinkies long ways and place cream side up in a 9 x 13 pan. Spread drained pineapple over Twinkies and sliced bananas over pineapple. Prepare pudding with 3 cups milk and spread over bananas. Spread Cool Whip over pudding. Sprinkle with nuts and let chill overnight for best results.

title: sesame cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Blend in almond extract and salt.
Add flour; mix well.
Shape tablespoonfuls of dough into balls and roll in sesame seed.
Place on ungreased baking sheets; flatten slightly.
Indent center of each and fill with preserves. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour 1/2 batter in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels, cream and butter over low heat stirring.
Sprinkle with 3/4 to 1 1/2 cups pecans and all the chocolate chips.
Add the rest of the batter.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients, then add the rest, in well-greased bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: lemon orange cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put cake mix in large bowl; set aside.
In another bowl, put 1/3 cup of juices, 1 cup water, 3 eggs and 1/3 cup oil.
Mix and add to cake mix. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: st. nicholas' bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Combine scalded milk, sugar and salt.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Blend in yeast.
Add eggs and 3 cups flour.
Beat until bubbly.
Add melted butter that has been cooled.
Sprinkle 1 cup flour over prepared fruits and nuts.
Reserve 1/2 cup flour for kneading.
Add rest and cardamon seed to batter.
Mix well.
Stir in fruit mixture.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board. Cover and let rest for 10 minutes.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl, greasing top of dough lightly.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 2 hours.
Divide dough into 6 equal portions.
Shape into loaves.
Place in well-greased 1 pound coffee cans.
Brush with melted butter; cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes.
Cool in pans for 5 minutes, then remove from pans and cool on racks. Drizzle with icing and sprinkle with colored sugar.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan (Bundt) and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pan while hot and ice or glaze.

title: popsicles
directions: Jell-O and Kool-Aid should be the same flavor, although you may mix certain other flavors together, such as orange/pineapple, etc.
Mix Jell-O, Kool-Aid and sugar together.
Add hot water and mix well.
Then pour in cold water and mix well.
Pour mixture into popsicle mold and freeze.

title: brown rice
directions: Cover bottom of skillet with oil.
Add 1 cup of rice.
When rice is brown, add ingredients.
Add 2 cups of water, 1/2 can tomato sauce, 1 bouillon, salt and pepper.
Stir once to mix ingredients.
Cover and simmer.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Cook an additional 30 to 35 minutes.

title: honey barbecue chicken
directions: Season chicken to desired taste, then flour chicken.
Fry over medium heat until golden brown.
Mix sauce and honey.
Pour over fried chicken; rotate chicken in sauce 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove chicken from sauce.
Easy as 1,2,3.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream potatoes.
Stir in butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Mix spices, salt and milk in potato mixture.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 70 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into small balls. Place on a cookie sheet and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy italian potatoes(microwave)
directions: Place potatoes in microwave-safe dish.
Drizzle with oil; sprinkle with basil, oregano, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover with waxed paper; microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; microwave 1 minute on High.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli tortellini
directions: Saute butter and garlic, boil broccoli (see package) and drain. Boil tortellini (see package) and drain.
Mix gently, broccoli, tortellini, butter and garlic.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Let cucumbers, salt and onion stand overnight.
Drain next morning, so salt will be all gone.
Let sugar and vinegar come to a boil.
Let cool.
Pour over drained pickles.
Let stand 24 hours.
Ready to serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf dish.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: wilma's egg rolls
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in wok or frying pan.
Stir-fry carrot, onion, celery, chop suey, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook about 3 minutes; drain and set aside.
In separate small frypan, mix soy sauce, wine and cornstarch; cook a few minutes and then pour over first mixture.
Mix well and allow to cool.
Place a portion of vegie mix and meat in corner of wrapper; roll until wrapper makes a triangle.
Moisten edges of wrapper with water so as to seal.
Fold in the ends of the wrapper and roll up.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.
I make large rolls using 2 tablespoons of mixture, but some like small ones better.

title: layered pea salad
directions: Layer first five ingredients alternately in glass bowl in order given.
Spread dressing over top of vegetables, sealing edges.
Sprinkle cheese on top, then sprinkle bacon crumbs.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 24 hours.
Toss well just before serving.

title: peach streusel pie
directions: In bowl, combine brown sugar and flour; mix well.
With pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Preheat oven to 400°.

title: german sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll dough 1/4 inch thick on a floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 350° and grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and butter, stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press 1/2 of this mixture into pan.
Beat cheese until fluffy; add condensed milk, vanilla and egg.
Mix well and pour over crumbs in pan then top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature then chill in refrigerator before cutting into bars.

title: soft peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the brown sugar, butter and peanut butter.
Add eggs, milk, baking powder, vanilla and flour.
Add chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir cornmeal, salt and soda together. Combine corn, eggs, buttermilk and shortening and mix with dry ingredients.

title: philadelphia cream cheese and olives
directions: Allow Philadelphia cream cheese to reach room temperature. Break up with fork; spoon in mayonnaise and add milk.
Cut up olives into small slices and mix in thoroughly.
Make small finger sandwiches or serve on cracked wheat bread as an inexpensive party treat.

title: ham sensations (40)
directions: Combine flour, cheese, pepper and butter. Gradually add water, mixing at low speed until dough forms. Knead on floured surface 12 times. Roll out dough, half at a time, to 14 x 10. Cut into four 7 x 5 pieces. Place a slice of ham on each. Sprinkle with crushed onions. Starting with 5-inch side, roll up jelly roll fashion; seal edge. Place seam side down on greased cookie sheet. Brush with milk. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cut each roll into 5 slices. Serve hot or cold.

title: boiled chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken breast; debone if desired.
Place chicken in a small stock pot; add some celery, onion and carrot and a piece of fresh ginger.
Add enough cold water to cover by 2 inches; bring to a boil.
Cook for 10 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and no sign of pink remains.
Do not overcook.

title: cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower in microwave approximately 9 minutes.
Spread mixture over it.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Microwave another minute or until melted.

title: chicken recipe
directions: Add butter and broth.
Add a little
more than half bag of dressing to mix.
Save remainder to add
on
top
of casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes
or
until
golden
brown. This makes a small casserole.

title: raspberry-nut strudel
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add flour, beating well.
Divide dough into 4 equal portions.
Wrap each in plastic wrap and chill.
Work with 1 portion of dough at a time; keep remaining dough chilled.

title: quickie fig cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a
bowl
and
mix thoroughly with a spoon.
(Be sure to
include
syrup from fig preserves. This is the only liquid and
sweetener
in	this
cake).
Pour into well-greased pan about 9 x	12-inches.
Bake
at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: royce's broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli (using even the stems) and onion.
Mix together with cheese; set aside.
Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar until creamy. Mix through salad.
(May seem dry.)
Top with bacon bits and chill one hour.
(This will turn out creamy.)
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and salt in small bowl; set aside.
Place egg white and water in medium bowl. Beat with electric mixer at medium speed until frothy but not stiff.
Pour pecans into egg white mixture; stir until coated. Add sugar mixture; stir until coated.
Spread on cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: hungarian flaky horns
directions: Sift flour into bowl; grate oleo into flour, then add sour cream and mix gently with hands as you would for pie dough.

Divide dough into 4 parts; roll each part out and fold into a square. Cover with waxed paper and let stand in refrigerator overnight. Roll out the next day, cut with a hot knife into squares and fill with desired filling.
Bake in 350° oven for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: rhubarb bread pudding
directions: Trim crusts from bread, then toast slices.
Cut toast into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place them in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Scald milk in saucepan.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Pour over toast cubes and let stand 15 minutes.
Combine eggs, sugar, cinnamon, salt and rhubarb.
Stir into bread mixture.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar.
Bake at 300° for about 50 minutes or until set.
Top with half and half or ice cream.

title: dill pickles
directions: Make a brine of vinegar, water and salt; bring to a boil. Place the dill, garlic and mustard seed in bottom of jar.
Pack cucumbers in jar and pour brine to within 1/2-inch of top.
Fasten lids and process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: crunchy chicken cheese
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Stir soup; pour over cheese.
Top with slice of tomato.
Combine margarine and dressing.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan layer pineapple and cherry pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix over.
Lay margarine across.
Layer coconut and walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Put popcorn in baking pan.
Put sugar, margarine, salt and syrup in a heavy, 3-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring until boiling begins.
Stop stirring and cook for 5 more minutes. Add 1/2 teaspoon soda and stir.
Pour over popcorn and stir to coat as evenly as possible.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Pour out on wax paper to cool.
Store in airtight containers.

title: roast in a crock-pot
directions: Heat oil

in large skillet. Add beef; season with salt and pepper. Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until browned. In 3 1/2 to 4-quart crock-pot, combine beef with all ingredients except green beans. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 8 hours.

title: grandma's no-bake fruit cake
directions: In a small pan, combine sugar, water and flavoring and bring to a low boil.
Allow to cool and pour half the syrup over the cake.
Refrigerate remainder of syrup and pour over cake the next day.
Let cake stay chilled or frozen for at least one more day and then slice and enjoy.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix well. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: scalloped cheese potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Combine the potatoes with the Cheddar cheese, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Taste for seasoning and blend in the egg yolk.
Beat the egg white lightly in a shallow bowl.
Combine the bread crumbs and Romano cheese in a second bowl.

Shape spoonfuls of the mashed potatoes into 20 even-sized balls and flatten each one slightly. Dip each croquette into the beaten egg white and then into the cheese-crumb mixture, being sure to coat each one evenly.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes on medium speed.
Bake in three layers for 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat thoroughly with bread soaked in milk or water.
Add seasoning, beat in eggs.
Mix well.
Pack into a well-greased loaf pan.
Spread top with catsup or chili sauce.
Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.
I add 3 or 4 slices of bacon on top.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and cocoa together in saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Take off fire; add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Spoon out on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients with the drained carrots and refrigerate overnight.
This keeps well 3 to 4 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and pour in batter.
Mix together in saucepan liquid from canned fruit.
Add hot water to make 2 cups, sugar and butter.
Stir and bring to boil, then pour over batter.
Pour fruit on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
May serve as is or in bowl with milk over it.

title: "zesty" chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken in 8 x 12-inch dish.
Pour salad dressing over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 400°.
Place rice, vegetables and 1/2 cup onion rings around and under chicken. Combine bouillon and Italian seasoning.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 2 or 3 minutes longer.

title: cooked soda dough
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook over medium heat and stir until mixture is too thick to stir.
Knead the mixture as it cools.
This has a different consistency from those made with flour.
Keep in an airtight container; add more water to rework dough when needed.

title: frito casserole
directions: Saute onion in small amount oil.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, garlic and catsup.
Brown and drain ground beef and add to mixture.
Line casserole dish with Fritos.
Pour all mixture on chips.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 10 minutes on 375°.

title: mexican string beans
directions: Cook onion in oil; add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
May serve with scrambled eggs.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve sugar well in water.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Form individual loaves with hands (approximately 3/4 cup each).
Freeze, then wrap individual loaves and place in Ziploc bags.
Use as needed.
Thaw, then top with barbecue sauce and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: lemon-zesty spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach thoroughly.
Drain and tear into bite-size pieces.
Combine spinach in a large bowl.
Cover tightly and chill.
Combine next 6 ingredients in an electric blender and blend well; store in refrigerator.
At serving time, pour dressing over vegetables.
Add sliced mushrooms and sprinkle bacon on top. Toss lightly.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add 1/2 hash browns.
Mix soup, sour cream and onion in separate bowl. Pour 1/2 over hash browns.
Sprinkle 1 cup of cheese on top. Cover with rest of hash browns.
Pour rest of soup mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover with corn flakes and 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: canned corn beef and rice
directions: Clean the chittlins by removing most of the fat attached to each piece, rinsing well as you go along.
Leave on a very small amount of fat.
Wash each piece thoroughly.
Place each cleaned piece in a very large pot.
When all are done, fill pot with water. Add red pepper, garlic, salt and regular pepper (black or white). Place the white potatoes on top of the chittlins and other ingredients, then cover the pot.
Cook until the chittlins are tender and well done.
Drain off the chittlins liquid.
Transfer the chittlins to a large plate and cut in serving size pieces.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Line a skillet with bacon; add 4 or more hamburger patties, depending on the number of people to serve.
Top with potato slices and carrots.
If you like onion, put a slice on each hamburger patty.
Cover skillet and put on high heat until bacon sizzles (about 1 minute).
Add 1/4 cup water and lower heat.
Cook about 30 minutes or until tender.

title: rodgrod med flode(red fruit pudding with cream)
directions: *Or substitute two 10-ounce packages of frozen berries.

title: peas and peanut salad
directions: Cook peas just slightly. Drain. Mix peas and peanuts together with mayonnaise and honey. Let stand at least 1 hour in the refrigerator before serving.

title: hungarian potatoes
directions: Mix butter, sour cream, salt and pepper (much easier to mix and pour if warm) and layer in this order in buttered pan:
potatoes, eggs, sour cream mixture and bread crumbs; repeat layers.
Top with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat and add bread.
Layer tomatoes sprinkled with sugar, pepper and salt, then bread crumb mixture, then cheese; repeat.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and paraffin to a good boil.
Test by spinning a thread.
Then add peanuts.
Sprinkle with soda and salt when almost done.

title: drunk roast
directions: Flour roast and brown in oil.
Add cooking wine, salt and pepper.

Cooking wine has salt added so be careful not to over salt. Bake in heavy covered pan at 350° for about 3 hours or until tender. May have to add a little water if needed. Remove meat and thicken juice with a little cornstarch and water.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Melt 1 square chocolate; set aside.
Mix cake according to directions on the package.
Makes a round 8-inch cake.
Pour into baking pan.
Pour melted chocolate over batter; cut in with a knife to mix.
Bake at 350° for about 27 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti; combine other ingredients, except cheese. Simmer until pepper and onions are tender.
In large dish, layer spaghetti, sauce and cheese twice.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: salsa
directions: Cook tomatoes 2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 hour.
Stir often.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: self filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Fill paper baking cups 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar together. Beat in egg and salt.
Sit in chocolate chips.
Drop 1 rounded teaspoon cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake as package directs.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Pit and slice dates.
Drain pineapple.
Cream shortening and sugar together thoroughly.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Sift flour with salt, baking powder and soda.
Blend about half of flour mixture into creamed mixture.
Add pineapple, then remaining flour.
Blend in vanilla, walnuts and dates.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Grate carrots.
Mix all ingredients well. Chill before serving.

title: veal casserole
directions: Season veal with salt and pepper.
Dip veal in egg-water mixture, then Italian seasoned bread crumbs.
Brown in oil and drain on paper towel.
Place in casserole.
Cover with tomato sauce and bake, covered with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and sprinkle casserole with Mozzarella cheese after removing foil.
Leave in hot oven for a few minutes to melt cheese.

title: oreo surprise
directions: Mix both containers of Cool Whip with Oreos that have been crushed until thoroughly mixed together.

title: old-fashioned creamy rice pudding
directions: Wash rice thoroughly; add the other ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake 3 hours in a slow oven (300°).
The mixture should not boil.

title: dill bites
directions: Wrap cream cheese around spear; wrap lunch meat around cheese. Slice 1-inch thick.
Insert toothpicks and serve.

title: barbecue sauce for pork
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Example:
Pour over pork roast, used for barbecue sauce on barbecue sandwiches, on ribs or any pork.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix margarine (melted), water and flour.
Roll out on floured wax paper and cut into 1 x 3-inch strips.
Remove chicken from broth, debone and put back in broth.
Bring to a boil and drop dumplings one at a time.
Cook until done on medium-low heat.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces and pound with a meat hammer.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat the meat with the seasoned flour.
In a large skillet, brown meat in hot oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until the meat is tender.

title: party rye
directions: Fry hamburger, sausage and cayenne pepper.
Drain grease. Combine cheese and oregano; mix well.
Place on party rye bread and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to cream mixture. Stir in oats and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: salsa
directions: Stir together all ingredients except tomato sauce. Place 1 cup of mixture and the tomato sauce in a blender. Puree. Stir into the remaining mixture. Cover and chill several hours before serving.

title: pralines
directions: Mix soda and buttermilk; then dissolve sugar.
Use a big saucepan and boil slowly into soft ball stage 234° (236° if damp weather).
Mixture turns brown as it cooks, but needs stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and add flavors, margarine and pecans.
Stir until it begins to look like its ready to sugar or cream.
Drop in small cakes on wax paper.
Makes about 30 pralines.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Wash and grind green tomatoes with coarse grind. Drain off juice. Cover with boiling water and let cool. Drain and repeat. Grind apples, raisins and suet. Add rest of ingredients. Combine all in large kettle. Bring to a boil and cook 1 hour. Pour in hot jars and seal. Makes about 9 quarts.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook broccoli as directed.
Beat Bisquick, milk, eggs and salt with a hand beater until smooth.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Pour into dish.
Bake until a knife inserted comes out clean, approximately 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and 10X sugar together until crumbly. Put in bottom of pie shell (save a little to put on top of pie).

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter, mix with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Blend in vinegar, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.
Very quick and easy.

title: sloppy joes en masse(that means for a whole bunch!)
directions: Brown hamburger meat slowly, then add the chopped onions, catsup and brown sugar.
Cook slowly until done.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Make hamburger into meatballs, cocktail size or to your liking.
Brown on a cookie sheet.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into small balls. Brown in skillet. Place in baking dish and add mushroom soup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Sift flour once, then measure.
Add baking powder and salt; sift 3 times.
Cream butter thoroughly and add sugar gradually. Continue creaming until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition. Stir in vanilla and coconut.
Fold in egg whites carefully.
Bake in a greased 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain excess fat; add other ingredients, except tortillas and cheese.
Dip tortillas into hot oil just long enough to soften.
Drain on paper towels.
Place 1/4 cup grated cheese on each tortilla; roll up each tortilla.
Place in skillet of sauce mix.
Cover and cook until heated through. Top with remaining 1/2 cup of cheese.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients. Add flour, baking soda and salt to creamed mixture and mix until well blended. Shape into rolls. Wrap in wax paper and chill. Slice and bake in 350° oven until brown. (Chopped nuts can be added to the batter before baking if desired.)

title: hot wine punch
directions: Combine and warm until butter melts (use a slow cooker).
Nice to serve at holiday time.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift the flour, then measure.
Sift the sugar; measure and divide into 2 equal parts.
Add 1/2 the sugar to flour, then sift together 4 times.
Add salt to egg whites; beat until foamy. Sprinkle cream of tartar over egg whites, then beat until stiff but not dry.
Fold in the remaining sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time. Add flavoring.
Fold in the sugar and flour mixture, 2 tablespoons at a time; mix well.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and nutmeg in a saucepan. Gradually stir in water.
Cook over moderately low heat (225°), stirring constantly, until thickened and clear.
Remove from heat. Add butter and lemon juice.
Stir until butter is melted.
Keep warm until serving time.

title: tuna bumstead
directions: Mix the salad type mixture together in a bowl.
Stuff the salad into the hot dog buns.
Wrap each one individually in aluminum foil, being sure to secure the foil tightly so that it is well covered and airtight.
These may be frozen at this time for future use or simply bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Add about 15 to 20 minutes if frozen.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Better if made day before serving.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: strawberry pudding desserts
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Make pudding as directed on package.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over angel food cake.
Next, fold in strawberries.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: quick microwave cake
directions: Smear 1/2 can frosting in bottom of microwave tube pan.
Mix remaining ingredients for 2 minutes using mixer on medium speed. Pour over frosting.
Bake 12 minutes on High, turning occasionally.
Leave in oven for 15 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and turn upside down on serving platter.
Ice top with remaining frosting, if desired.

title: ham rolls or spam
directions: *Or, use 4 teaspoons baking powder in place of the cream of tartar and soda.

title: brandied stuffed dates
directions: Soak dates in brandy, turning occasionally until most of the brandy is absorbed, about 24 hours.
Place a pecan in each date. Press to close.
Roll in sugar.
Store airtight in refrigerator.

title: green chili stew
directions: Brown meat and potatoes together.
Stir constantly to prevent sticking.
Drain excess fat.
Add green chili, tomatoes, garlic salt, onion powder and water.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with flour tortillas or Huevos Rancheros Tome Style.

title: grandpa sweet's dandelion wine
directions: Combine all ingredients in 8-quart or larger kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Stir in one package of dry yeast.
Let stand in pot for 3 days.
Skim off dandelions and rinds.
Bottle* and keep in dry place.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour over vanilla wafers in tin foil cupcake holders on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 14 minutes or 350° for 20 minutes.
When cool fill with cherry or blueberry pie filling.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart in pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Melt one stick butter or oleo in a pan, pour it in the batter, add drained fruit of your choice. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage bits
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: easy chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Blend in eggs.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour batter into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle a few mini chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool.
For best results, refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; freeze in muffin cups or in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve over lettuce leaf.

title: 90 minute dinner rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup flour with sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine to 120°.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup flour; beat 2 minutes.
Stir in additional flour to make soft dough.

title: crockpot applebutter
directions: Combine all ingredients in crockpot.
Cook until it is a thick applesauce texture or preserves texture.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and milk.
Add corn.
Pour into a pan in which margarine has been melted.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam, then layer rolls, nuts, pudding and brown sugar.
Layer until 3/4 full.
You may dip rolls in mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon, then layer.
Allow to thaw overnight at room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian cheese dip
directions: Mix in bowl the cream cheese and crushed pineapple.
Chop green onions and green pepper.
Add to mixture.
Serve with Wheat Thins or your favorite crackers.

title: million dollar chicken
directions: In a large Dutch oven, place chicken at bottom, then add onion slices, carrots, peas and green beans.
Add spices over chicken and vegetables.
Add butter and white wine.
Mix sour cream and soup; pour over all ingredients.
Add sliced potatoes.*
Put lid on and bake for 3 hours at 300° to 325°.

title: scotcheroos-bar cookies
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan. Cook over moderate heat until mixture bubbles. Remove from heat and add peanut butter. Mix well. Add Rice Krispie's- stir until well blended. Press mixture into a buttered 13 x 9
pan. Melt both morsels together over low heat or microwave; when blended spread over cookie mixture. Cool until firm. Cut into bars.

title: persimmon roll
directions: Mix together; roll in graham cracker crumbs.
I crush a few more than 24.
Chill.
Slice and serve with whipped cream or you can eat it plain.

title: candied cubes
directions: Peel and dice apples in large pan.
Add all ingredients.
Let boil until apples are glazed or transparent.
Good for freezing.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and dry broccoli and cauliflower.
Break into florets. Add onions and raisins.

title: taco salad
directions: Taco Sauce:
Stir together stewed tomatoes, sugar, oregano, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and pepper sauce.
Using edges of spoon, break up large tomato pieces.
Stir in green peppers and onion; set aside.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine pineapple (with juice) and oranges.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
The following day, drain well, reserving liquid.
Cook liquid with sugar and cornstarch, over low heat, until thickened.
Cool.
Blend the thickened liquid with oranges and pineapple.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream brown sugar, Crisco and egg.
Mix flour, salt and soda. Add milk; mix well.
Add rhubarb.
Mix sugar and cinnamon, sprinkle over batter.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cookie monster's sugar cookies
directions: Put butter and sugar in a bowl; blend well.
Crack eggs over mixture; add vanilla and mix.
Put flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl and mix.
Put everything together and mix well.
Put dough in icebox to chill for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break linguine into 4ths and cook, drain and rinse.
Mix altogether.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Stir a couple of times through the evening.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Mix sugar, water and juice; boil to soft ball stage or 240° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from burner; add orange rind and pecans and stir until syrup looks cloudy.
Pour onto heavy wax paper as mixture cools.
Break apart.

title: orange julius
directions: Any concentrated juice will vary recipe.
Blend all in blender.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Simmer for 1 to 2 hours so flavors blend.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with sauce.

title: carol's chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Three cans of chicken would work as well.

title: spanish hamburger #2
directions: Follow directions as for Spanish Hamburger #1.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil and seasonings; pour over crackers and toss.
Seal tightly for several hours to let liquid absorb.

title: beef and peppers
directions: Saute garlic in shortening.
Add meat and brown well. Sprinkle with salt and sugar.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally or until meat is tender.
Stir in green pepper and gravy.
Simmer until green pepper is tender.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil, skin and bone chicken.
Chop.
Save broth.
Mix all ingredients except cheeses, tortillas and chicken.
Add 3/4 cup chicken broth.

title: pineapple orange salad
directions: Heat pineapple in juice until boiling.
Add jello and mix well. Combine with buttermilk gradually.
Add Cool Whip, apples and nuts. Let chill until firm.

title: big aunty's butter biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift flour, baking powder and sugar. Cut the Crisco into the dry ingredients.
Stir in eggs and milk until mixture is slightly wet.
Place butter in 9-inch round or square cake pan and melt in oven.
Remove pan.
Flour hands and quickly shape batter into desired portions and place in butter. Bake for about 10 minutes.

title: paper sack pie
directions: Peel and slice enough apples to fill pie shell.
Mix the following and pour over apples:
flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt. Mix together sugar, flour and butter and sprinkle this topping over pie.
Place in small paper bag and tie with wire and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Combine milk and water, blend well.
Then add vanilla pudding and whip.
Next, chill 5 minutes.
Whip whipping cream and fold into pudding.
In a bowl, layer vanilla pudding, vanilla wafers and bananas.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix together flour, salt, cayenne and mustard.
Add butter and mix well.
Blend in cheese thoroughly.
Add egg yolk and enough water to make a stiff dough.
Roll out thinly and cut into narrow straws.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes until golden brown.

title: chicken vermouth
directions: Marinate chicken in dressing overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken that has been drained of dressing.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: heartwarming beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a large Dutch oven, cover and bake 4 to 5 hours at 250°.

title: ellie's cole slaw
directions: Grate the first 3 items together.
Cut 1/2 jar sweet pickles; add to other ingredients, then add 1/3 to 1/2 of
the juice from pickles.
Add enough mayonnaise to hold together.

title: pecan praline salad
directions: Put sugar into heavy skillet and place on high heat.
Stir until sugar melts and caramelizes.
Add pecans and toss until nuts are coated.
Turn out onto buttered piece of foil.
Separate nuts and let cool.
Wash spinach and lettuce to remove all sand.
Dry thoroughly.
Place into salad bowl.
Top with mushrooms and onion. Sprinkle with tarragon leaves.
Just before serving, drizzle oil evenly over leaves.
Sprinkle with vinegar, salt and pepper. Toss.
Add mandarin orange segments.
Top with the pecans.
Makes 4 servings.

title: prize potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and eggs while they are
still warm/hot to touch. Cut into eighths.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in a glass bowl for at least 2 to 3 hours. Best when prepared at least 1 day in advance. Serves 6.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat juice and add gelatin.
Let cool until slightly
set.
Beat gelatin with electric beater until smooth. Fold
in
pineapple,
celery,
nuts, cream cheese and beaten cream (unsweetened).
Pour mixture into glass bowl and refrigerate.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix together in a large punch bowl and add ice or use an ice ring.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread coconut on bottom of a well-greased 15 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
Spread pecans over coconut.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box and pour on top of coconut and pecans.
Mix butter, cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of cake batter. Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Let cool and serve.

title: "banana pepper" in a jar
directions: Wash peppers (banana and bell).
Cut into strips, removing seeds.
Drain until almost dry.
Pack into clean sterilized quart jars (pack tightly).
Add 2 to 3 hot peppers to a jar.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon alum to a jar of peppers.
Sprinkle over the top.
Pour hot boiling vinegar over pepper filling jar to approximately 1/2-inch from top of jar, making sure pepper is covered with vinegar.
Wipe jar rim dry.
Seal with hot sterilized seals and lids.
Let stand for approximately 2 weeks before opening.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cook over low heat the apricots, sugar and water until apricots are tender and most of the water is absorbed, approximately 20 minutes.
Sieve fruit; set aside.
Cream butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and salt slowly.
Spread evenly on bottom of 9 x 9-inch greased pan. Spread apricot mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool; cut into 1 x 2-inch squares.
Decorate with almonds or coconut.

title: elegant chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until tender and cut into bite size pieces. Reserve cup of stock.
Cook noodles in remaining stock plus necessary water.
Blend sour cream, mushroom soup and 1 cup chicken stock.
Stir into mixture of noodles, beef and chicken. Pour into 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with paprika and bacon. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken-broccoli
directions: In shallow casserole, arrange broccoli, topped with chicken. Combine soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese. Combine butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.

title: braised german cabbage
directions: Combine ingredients in large skillet.
Cover and cook on a low flame 20 to 25 minutes, or until cabbage is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes and cook in skins until done.
Cool.
Remove skins and dice.
Add to potatoes the chopped onions, stuffed green olives, dill weed, mayonnaise and salt and pepper.
(May substitute salad dressing for mayonnaise if taking to a picnic where it can't be kept cold.)

title: irish scone
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center and add milk and melted butter.
Mix lightly with wooden spoon.
Knead lightly.
Mixture should be slack, not wet.
Fold in raisins.
Place in prepared pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
After removing cake from pan, wet it lightly with cold water.

title: potato fondue dip
directions: Boil potatoes and leave in jackets.
Heat remaining ingredients in fondue pot.
Keep on low temperature.
Dip potatoes and eat immediately.

title: may harley's molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a 3 or 4-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Sift baking soda, spices, salt and flour together. Add sugar, molasses and egg to cooled shortening and beat well. Stir in flour, forming a stiff dough.
Chill thoroughly before forming into 1-inch balls.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll cookies in granulated sugar and place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 50.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cream together the butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add the egg yolk, flour and salt.
Grease a 14 x 10-inch pan well.
Pat batter on pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove; spread the apricot jam on top.
Have the egg whites beaten stiff with 1 cup sugar and the vanilla mixed in them.
Spread on top of jam; bake for 20 minutes.
Cut in bars while hot.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Bring to boil, then remove from heat.
This sauce is good for chicken or pork.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: olive marinade
directions: Cut a slit in each olive.
Fill a jar with olives.
Cover with marinade.
Olives will keep many months and improve with marinating.
You can also use this over salad or as a marinade for steak tips, lamb tips or pork tips.
Enjoy!

title: applesauce cake(sugar-free)
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar substitute.
Combine baking soda and applesauce; add to creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into nonstick 7 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
When cake is cooled, cut into 15 equal slices.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients; add flour and sugar, then add buttermilk, soda, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Mix all together in bowl.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate-pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put flour, sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa, baking powder and salt in a deep dish baker.
Stir to mix well.
Add milk and oil.
Stir until well blended.
Sprinkle brown sugar, remaining 1/4 cup cocoa and chocolate chips over the batter.
Mix vanilla with water and pour evenly over the top (try almond extract instead of vanilla sometime).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until surface looks dry and brownie-like.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.
Makes 9 servings; 243 calories each.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Heat oil in deep frying pan.

Add onions, garlic and brown; add meat and brown slowly. Heat tomato juice, puree, and paste in deep kettle (3 qt. size). Add meat mixture, celery, green pepper, parsley, and other seasonings. Simmer slowly for 1 1/2 hours. Remove bay leaf. Add sliced olives; simmer 10 minutes longer. Serve over hot spaghetti. Top with Parmesan cheese. Makes 2 quarts spaghetti sauce. Freezes well.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, beating well.
Place batter in a buttered bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and slice.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Form into balls.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Bake frozen balls in 350° oven for 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 60 to 70 bite-size balls.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place cut apples in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan or deep dish baking pan.
Mix together the white sugar and cinnamon; pour
over apples.
Mix the brown sugar, flour and margarine together until mixture is crumbly; place on top of apple mixture.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until apples are soft when pierced with a fork.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: fried squash
directions: Wash and slice yellow summer squash.
Roll in corn meal.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Fry in a small amount of bacon drippings until brown.
(Could use scrambled egg mixture first and the cornmeal.)

title: caramel-fudge chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions. Stir in 3/4 cup chocolate chips. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Immediately poke holes in the cake with a meat fork or skewer. Spread caramel and fudge toppings over cake. Cool on a wire rack. Frost with whipped topping. Sprinkle with toffee bits and remaining chocolate chips. Store in the refrigerator. Yield: 12 to 15 servings.

title: layered dessert
directions: Mix well and spread in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all above ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: susan's secret ham dip
directions: Mix all together.
Garnish with paprika and additional parsley flakes.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: hamburger and beans
directions: Put in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco.
Add milk and mix well.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased pan and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: red hot wings
directions: Combine last 9 ingredients.
Deep fry wings.
Let simmer in sauce for 10 minutes.

title: crab cotillion
directions: Blend soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Stir crab into mixture. Blend half of shredded cheese into mixture.
Stir in the noodles. Put in a 1-quart casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (from room temperature).

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. In a large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients. Close bag and shake, or toss in bowl, until evenly coated.
Spray 9 x 13 inch pan with Pam: arrange potatoes in pan; discard bag. Bake uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: quick pigs in a blanket
directions: Chop cabbage into medium pieces.
Spread cabbage in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brown meat and onion in large skillet.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture over cabbage.
Heat tomato soup and water to boiling; pour over all ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover baking dish with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.
Makes 4 servings; this may be doubled.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until brown, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes minimum.
The longer it simmers the better it tastes.
Good over rice or noodles.

title: ham rolls
directions: Pat ham slices dry with a paper towel.
Spread cream cheese in a thin layer over ham.
Place one onion on ham and roll up. Put in fridge to set.
When ready to serve, cut rolls into slices. Arrange on platter and serve.

title: spicy cheese omelet
directions: Pour beaten egg into preheated, nonstick skillet coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Cook until slightly firm.
Combine cottage cheese and seasonings and spread over half of egg.
Fold the egg in half.
Cover and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serves 1.

title: hash browns au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together in oblong Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with more shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy oven soft chicken tacos
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Place tortillas on baking sheets.

title: bigos venison meat
directions: Wash sauerkraut and cook until tender.
Cut bacon and fry. Add onion and meat to fry until meat is tender.
Add Polish sausage and sauerkraut and boil until the flavors blend.
Season to taste. Add sauteed mushrooms.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes in a well greased and floured pan.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
Remove stems, chop stems and set aside.

title: pink stuff
directions: Use any other fresh fruit that you want.

title: potato candy
directions: Add potatoes to sugar slowly until it thickens.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on wax paper.
Roll out sugar mixture (thin) and spread with peanut butter.
Roll into a log and cut.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix as stated on package (bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan).
After cake has cooled, spread drained pineapple on top.
