Make cream cheese icing by mixing the butter, cream cheese and vanilla together and gradually add the box of confectioners sugar (may not need entire box of sugar); continue to beat icing until it appears glossy.
Spread onto cake and refrigerate.

title: fall fruit souffle salad *
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add lemon juice and salad dressing.
Blend with rotary beater, add cold water and blend. Pour into freezing tray and chill until firm around the edges. Remove from tray and whip until fluffy.
Fold in fruit.
Chill.

title: glazed meatballs(sweet and sour)
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onions, milk, egg and next 4 seasonings. Gently shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in a large skillet; drain off fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet until jelly is melted, stirring constantly.
Add meatballs and stir until coated.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve hot in a chafing dish.
Put toothpicks beside the chafing dish.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat, onions, green peppers and garlic.
Cook until onoins are transparent.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, paste, salt, pepper and other spices.
Cover and simmer one hour.
Remove bay leaf.
Arrange in layers of sauce, noodles and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: oatmeal honey gems(diabetic recipe)
directions: Mix honey, oil and eggs with wire whisk.
Add almond extract, orange peel, salt, oatmeal and coconut.
Stir until well blended. Bake at 400° for 7 minutes or until tops are light brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare meat with seasoning mix.
Let cool.
Chop lettuce, cucumbers and tomatoes into small pieces and toss together in large bowl with all other ingredients.
Crush Doritos and put into salad and toss.

title: spanish cabbage
directions: Fry hamburger and diced onion.
Drain off grease.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder and stir.
Add tomatoes and sugar.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cut up cabbage in a large pot.
Pour meat mixture over the cabbage and add 1 cup of water.
Stir from time to time. Cook on medium heat for 1 hour.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Soften ice cream.
Melt oleo.
Add cracker crumbs and chopped nuts.
Spread half of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat pudding, coconut, flavoring and milk until thick.
Fold in ice cream.
Put on top of crumbs in pan.
Spread
with Cool Whip. Cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Refrigerate.
Can be made night before and covered with Saran Wrap.
You may use instant coconut cream pudding and omit the coconut and flavoring.

title: barbecue sauerkraut
directions: Mix ketchup and sauerkraut in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon and brown sugar on top.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: minestrone
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and rinse.
Add all other ingredients except Parmesan.
Cook until noodles are tender.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Cook sausage, breaking it up in pan.
Saute onion and celery in drippings.
Combine all ingredients in 1.5 casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for the milk and bread crumbs, then add scalded milk and mix well.
Then add bread crumbs and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: swedish molasses cake
directions: Grease and flour 8 x 8-inch pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Combine first four ingredients.
Cut in shortening with fork.
Remove 1/2 cup and set aside for topping.
Combine molasses, soda and sour milk.
(To make sour milk, place 1 tablespoon vinegar in measuring cup and fill with milk to make 1 cup.)
Add molasses/milk mixture to dry mixture and stir with fork until just moistened.
Do not beat.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cover with crumb topping.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: triple brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as instructed on the box.
Before baking, add the semi-sweet white chocolate and peanut butter chips.
Pour into the pan and sprinkle on the nuts.
Bake as directed on the box.
May make as cookies by following the conversion recipe on the box.

title: choc pudding pie
directions: Butter a deep dish 12-inch pie pan.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, flour, powder, salt and nuts.
Set aside.
Melt bitter chocolate, butter and milk (can use 2 tablespoons cocoa powder, 4 tablespoons butter and 1/2 cup milk instead, but do not heat).
Combine the flour mixture with the cooled chocolate mixture.
Pour into the pie pan. Mix the brown sugar, 1/2 cup sugar and cocoa; sprinkle on top.

title: mexican manicotti
directions: Combine uncooked ground beef, beans, chili powder and oregano. Spoon into uncooked shells.
Place in greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Combine water and picante sauce.
Pour over shells.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before baking.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover.
Spoon sour cream over top, sprinkle with cheese, onion and olives.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: peanut-butter cinnamon brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
In a small bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in peanut butter.

title: peanut butter crunch bars
directions: In
medium saucepan, cook together white sugar and corn syrup until it comes to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter (either smooth or crunchy).
Remove from heat.
Prepare a large bowl, lightly buttered,
with
cornflakes.
Pour
hot
mixture
over cornflakes and mix well.
Then press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 1 1/2 cups bran.
Let stand while mixing together all other ingredients, except remaining bran.
Add the remaining dry bran and soaked bran.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator.
Keeps about 6 weeks.
Bake as needed in 400° oven. Bake in small muffin tins for about 12 minutes; bake larger tins for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach pie (butter)(spanakopita)
directions: Wash spinach; allow to drain overnight in a colander.
Cut the coarse stems off and discard.
Chop spinach and green onions in a large mixing bowl.
Add crumbled cheese, unbeaten eggs and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour 1/2 of the melted butter over spinach mixture; toss lightly to combine all ingredients.

title: easy white cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together, then add Crisco, milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes, then add egg whites and beat 2 minutes again.
If you like, you can fold in batter 1/2 cup coconut or pink food coloring and teaberry flavoring.
Makes 2 layer pans or one 13 x 9-inch.

title: margaret's rolls
directions: Combine yeast in warm water; set aside.
Put sweet milk, shortening, sugar and salt in a pot.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Set in sink of cold water until cool.
Add 2 beaten eggs, yeast mixture and flour.

title: dump cake
directions: Place pineapple in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Add cherry pie filling on top.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix and spread evenly with spatula.
Melt butter and pour over cake mixture. Garnish with chopped pecans.
Place in oven for 50 minutes until top is lightly browned.
Delicious! Enjoy!

title: mama's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; keep broth.
Skin and debone chicken.
Take celery soup and mix with 1/2 can of chicken broth.
Put egg noodles in chicken broth and let boil until tender.
Drain and layer vegetables, celery soup (with broth), chicken and noodles in a casserole dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add lemon juice and vanilla; blend well.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add the dry mixture to the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well after each addition.
Pour into prepared pan; bake 20 to 25 minutes or until the center is set.
Cool on a wire rack for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 12 servings.

title: smoked trout mousse
directions: In the bowl of a food processor, puree the Ricotta until smooth (consistency of sour cream). Scrape it into a bowl. Fold in half the trout, then the horseradish, scallions, dill and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper. Fold in remaining trout and chill.

title: spareribs with kraut
directions: Season ribs with salt and pepper.
Combine kraut, carrots, tomato juice, brown sugar, caraway seed and apple.
Place together kraut mixture and ribs in Dutch oven.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours or until ribs are done.
Goes well with baked sweet potatoes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken noodle and vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan, bring broth to boiling.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch cubes and add to broth.
Add carrot, celery, chicken, rosemary, basil and poultry seasoning and bring to boiling.
When broth boils, reduce heat.
Add noodles.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 7 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and noodles are tender.
Serves 3.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender
until
well
mixed. Pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes; turn oven down to 350° and bake 35 minutes.

title: cabbage plus
directions: Toss with salad dressing listed below.

title: christmas ornament recipe
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then add applesauce and glue.
Stir to combine.
Work with hands 2 to 3 minutes until mixture is smooth and ingredients are fully mixed.
Divide into 4 portions.
Roll each portion to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut dough with cookie cutters of desired shapes.
Use a straw or toothpick to make a hole near the top of the ornament.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix snowdrift, brown sugar and eggs well. Add buttermilk, sift together dry ingredients and stir into mixture. Add pecans, dates and candied cherries. Chill dough one hour. Drop with teaspoon about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet. Top cookie with pecan halve or half of cherry. Bake at 400° for 10 - 12 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: tomato chow chow
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender. Place into saucepan and cook for about 20 minutes; put into clean canning jars.

title: extraordinary chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, sugars, vanilla and eggs in large bowl with spoon.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded spoonful (about 1 tablespoon) about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 4 dozen cookies.

title: no fuss meatball appetizer(or can use wieners.)
directions: Combine soy sauce, chili sauce, jelly and mustard. Place meatballs in crock-pot and pour sauce over them. Let them cook 3 to 4 hours on low.

title: dip
directions: Mix well and serve at room temperature.

title: make ahead egg casserole
directions: Mix bread, cheese, sausage, green pepper and onion.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Whisk eggs and milk.
Pour over top. Cover dish with foil and freeze.

title: marinated pea salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small saucepan. Bring mixture to a boil and boil 1 minute. Let cool completely. Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl and toss lightly. Pour marinade over vegetable mixture; stir gently. Cover salad and refrigerate overnight. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: mini meatball soup
directions: In a deep pot over medium heat add oil, chopped carrots, celery and onions and bay leaves.
Season with salt and pepper. Cover pot and cook veggies for 5 or 6 minutes, stirring occasionally.
While the veggies cook, combine meat, egg, garlic, grated cheese, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Uncover your soup and add broth and water to pot.
Increase heat to high and bring soup to a boil.
When soup boils, reduce heat a bit and start to roll meat mixture into small balls, dropping them straight into the pot.
You are making meat dumplings that will cook in the broth.
When you are done rolling the meat, add pasta to the soup and stir.
Cover and simmer soup 10 minutes.
When pasta is tender, stir in chopped spinach in batches.
When spinach has wilted into the soup, the soup is done and ready to serve. Adjust your seasonings.

title: party chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise, soup and chestnuts together.
Add celery and chicken.
Mix butter and enough dressing to generously cover a casserole.
Put chicken mixture into 3-quart greased casserole. Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix avocados, onion, chili, lemon or lime juice, cilantro and salt.
Stir in tomato.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 1 1/2 cups dip.

title: "roosevelt dinner"
directions: Slice potatoes and place in casserole. Slice carrots on top of potatoes. Add peas and slice onions on top of peas.
Add pork chops, salt and pepper. Pour on tomato soup and bake in 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: lemon delight pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, sugar and 1/4 cup water in saucepan. Blend in egg.
Add remaining water.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a full boil and is thickened.
Cool about 5 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Measure one cup, cover and cool completely.
Pour remaining filling into pie shell.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Brown bacon, onion and green pepper. Add pimentos, peas, chicken and ripe olives. Mix with cooked spaghetti. Add cheese (may be used in or on top).

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix unsweetened Kool-Aid with sugar, juice and water.
Chill until ready to serve.
Before serving, add Sprite.
Makes approximately 5 quarts.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Mix oil with sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in molasses and vinegar.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger. Add to molasses mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful in 1/4 cup sugar and form balls.
Cover with sugar.
Bake on ungreased pan at 350° for 8 minutes.
They rise and get light brown.
Watch and take from oven as they begin to fall.
I believe 1/4 cup more flour is better so cookies will not be so flat.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Make cake mix as directed. Take cream cheese, egg, sugar and salt and mix together. Then add chocolate chips. Fill cupcake holders 1/2 full, then add spoonful of mixture. Bake as cake mix directs.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and margarine and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar (can add a few drops of milk to mix well).
Spread this mixture over graham cracker crust. Then spread pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip or Dream Whip, using directions on box.
Chill 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.

title: infusa placenta(no you don't eat the placenta!  it means "pleasing mixture!")
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put in cherry pie filling mix, then cover with drained pineapple chunks and then with the dry cake mix. Over this pour butter, then coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream on top.

title: sally ann cookies
directions: Mix well and chill at least 1 hour.
Roll out (not too thin). Cut with empty Spam can. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Set aside 2/3 of the cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, margarine and beaten eggs.
Stir by hand (spoon) until mixture is crumbly.
Press the mixture evenly over the bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: parsonage punch
directions: Combine fruit juices, honey and cherry juice.
Chill.
Pour into punch bowl.
Spoon in vanilla ice cream.
Resting bottle or cup on rim, carefully pour in the ginger ale, stirring gently. Serve immediately.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: delicious punch
directions: Use 2 cups hot water to dissolve Jell-O.
Add quart of cold water to mixture.
Place all ingredients in large container and mix.
Sweeten to taste.

title: festive egg squares
directions: Layer sausage, mushrooms, green onions, tomatoes and cheese in greased baking dish 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Beat remaining ingredients; pour over sausage mixture.
Cook uncovered in 350° preheated oven until golden brown.
Let set about 30 minutes and cut into 12 (3-inch) squares.
Great for brunch!

title: herbed spinach bake
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour two small loaf pans or one regular pan. Preheat oven to 350°. Put ingredients into bowl. Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes. Pour into pans. Bake for approximately 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean and dry.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar, butter and 1 1/2 c. water in a small stainless steel, glass or enamel saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves. Combine cornstarch and remaining water in a small mixing bowl; mix well with a wire whisk; add to syrup mixture, mixing well. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture clears and thickens. Add lemon rind and juice; cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes. Combine egg yolks and milk in a small mixing bowl, mixing well; add a small amount of warm sauce, mixing well. Add back to sauce mixture in saucepan, mixing well. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; remove from heat. Sauce may be stored in refrigerator and reheated. It may be necessary to beat with a wire whisk before reheating.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Butter a 2 quart casserole. Prepare pasta as directed.
Drain.
Put pasta into casserole.
Cut butter into tablespoons and place on pasta.
Cut cheese thinly (to melt evenly).
Place on pasta.
Pour milk over top.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Stir to mix in cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes more, stirring often to prevent browning.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning. Spread in large pan.
Spread taco sauce over mixture.
Top with chopped lettuce, chopped tomatoes, sliced olives and shredded cheese.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: In skillet cook sausage, stirring to separate into bits. Remove meat.
Pour off all but 1/4 cup of fat drippings.
Add vinegar, oil, Worcestershire sauce and basil. Heat until boiling.

title: chicken biscuit stew
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 10-inch ovenproof skillet, melt margarine; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add chicken, onion, peas and carrots.
Simmer until hot and bubbly.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Arrange biscuits over hot chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: dilly cheese bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moist.
Spoon batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, until golden brown.

title: fried pie(apple)
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Cook over low heat until apples are flexible.
Add sugar.
Mix flour with water in jar; shake vigorously until a paste.
Stir into apples; cook until quite thick.
Add cinnamon and butter; mix well.
Let cool before using.

title: out of this world pie
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the cherry pie filling, pineapple, sugar, cornstarch and food coloring; cook until thick. Remove from heat and stir in jell-o; allow to cool.
Add the sliced bananas and chopped nuts.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells and chill well.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Bring to a boil the first 5 ingredients.
Let cool.
Shred lettuce.
Dice pepper and onion.
Grate carrot.
Mix all vegetables together and pour brine over them.
Freeze until needed.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl until dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or until slightly thickened.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle top with corn flake crumbs and drizzle 1/4 cup melted butter over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: barbecued ground beef
directions: Cook the ground
beef
in frypan or small pot until the meat is done.
Drain grease from meat and return the meat back in the pot.
Combine
the
onion,
the
salt, the vinegar, the brown sugar, the
ketchup,
and
the barbecue sauce; mix well. Add to the ground
beef
and
mix well.
Heat over a low fire, stirring frequently until
hot.
Serve
over bun or in a plate with cole slaw, potato salad
or
potato chips.
Serves 6 to 9 people.
A treat for the kids.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with the chips and nuts.
Bake at 350 oven for 30 minutes.

title: never fail oil crust
directions: Stir together flour, salt and wheat germ.
In measuring cup combine oil and cold water.
Add into flour all at once.
Roll into 2 balls.
Roll out each ball between 2 sheets wax paper.
(To keep paper from shifting, dampen area where paper is placed.)
Bake sheets in 425° oven for 10 minutes.

title: no-bake banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding and milk; whip.
Add cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk and half of Cool Whip; mix in a large dish.
Layer the mixture, vanilla wafers and bananas.
Repeat layers until all mixture is used, ending with mixture on top.
Use half of Cool Whip for topping.
Sprinkle crushed wafers on top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into uncooked crust.
Cook in 400° oven for first 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 30 minutes or longer.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into walnut size balls. Place meatballs on wax paper lined cookie sheet and freeze until solid.
Store in freezer bags until ready to cook.
When ready, cover with sauce.
Cook in a 9 x 13 baking pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pudding cake
directions: Bake sheet cake.
When completely cooled, mix pudding according to directions.
Spread on cooled cake.
Drain pineapple. Sprinkle pineapple over pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal pound cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: corn bread pie
directions: Cook beef and onion in frying pan until done.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes; set aside.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, margarine, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and melted butter.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish with 4 tablespoons butter.
Line dish with pretzel mixture.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 375°.
Let cool completely. Beat the cream cheese, Cool Whip and 10x sugar well.
Add to pretzel layer. Add 2 cups boiling water to jello, then add the strawberries.
Let cool and thicken.
Add to the top of the cream cheese and refrigerate.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Miracle Whip, prepared mustard and Chinese noodles.
Add the Miracle Whip.
Mix the prepared mustard.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours to blend flavors.
Toss with the Chinese noodles.

title: adam and eve pudding
directions: Cook apples in a small amount of water until soft, sweeten to taste.
Place in greased pie dish (8 x 8-inch Pyrex or similar); allow to cool.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Blend margarine with cake mix (use pie crust blender until crumbs).
Put cherries in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over cherries with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until golden brown.
Can be served warm with ice cream.

title: chicken chili
directions: Saute chicken in margarine until lightly browned, about 3 minutes.
Add beans, tomatoes, broth and chili seasoning mix. Bring to a boil, breaking up tomatoes with edge of spoon.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Bring mixture back to a boil. Stir in rice and peppers, cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes, fluff with fork.
Makes 7 1/2 cups or 4 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together.
Boil this mixture and mix.
Drop this batter on wax paper.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish in a single layer.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over chicken.
Baste every 15 minutes, baking at 325° to 350° for 1 1/4 hours (until brown).
Serve with wild rice pilaf.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Saute onions and chilies in melted butter.
Mix chicken and mushroom soup.
Dip tortillas in soup mixture.
Layer tortillas, chicken, soup, onions and cheese.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomatoes gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease large baking dish with oil.
Cut tomatoes crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Layer 1/2 tomato slices in dish.
Sprinkle with half spices.
Repeat layers.
Top with breadcrumbs; drizzle with oil.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade saltless sauerkraut(7 day method)
directions: You will also need a container to hold a gallon of liquid (glass, well glazed clay or other impermeable material; crock with cover), flat plate slightly smaller than the inner surface of container and several freshly scrubbed smooth stones.

title: italian style rump roast
directions: Arrange meat with fat side up in heavy casserole with lid. Combine garlic, fennel seed, pepper and oil to make a paste.
Rub paste over meat.
Drape bacon slices over meat.
Pour wine into pan.
Place a piece of waxed paper over the meat, fitting it on the meat, with edges extending up around edges of casserole (ensures a close fit of cover).
Place cover on.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours, until meat is tender.

title: granddaughter cookies
directions: Mix as given and roll in a roll.
Put in fridge for 30 minutes.
Slice and bake at 350°.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes.
Place chicken in shallow baking pan.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: irish cream
directions: Blend in blender and then refrigerate overnight.

title: chili
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until transparent.
In 5-quart pot, brown beef, 1/3 at a time.
Mix in green chilies and cook for 2 minutes.
Add all ingredients to beef and mix well.
Cook on low heat for 3 hours and serve.

title: divinity
directions: Make a pan of ice water.
Set mixing bowl in water.
Add milk, sweetener and 1/3 cup of water to mixing bowl.
Add extract mix. In a small pan, soften the gelatin in 1/3 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
To keep gelatin from getting tough, with an electric mixer at high speed, begin to whip milk in bowl, submerged in the ice water.
This helps it to whip quicker.
Slowly add the gelatin mix. Continue to whip until like whipped cream.
Spoon onto wax paper, freeze until ready to eat.

title: cherry relish
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, except the pecans.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Add pecans; cook 3 minutes longer.
Pour
into sterilized jars and seal.

title: ann's rolls
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm. Add shortening and sugar.
Shortening does not have to melt.
Add yeast. Stir and let stand 5 minutes. Add flour and salt. Roll out, cut and fold into Parker House rolls.
Let rise 3 or 4 hours or freeze.
Easy.

title: stuffing for baked fish
directions: Soak bread in cold water until soft, mash smooth, add butter, onion, parsley and a little milk.
Mixture must be just firm enough to keep its shape.
Stuff fish, sewing the opening.
If a dry crumbly stuffing is preferred, omit soaking and use half cracker crumbs.
Capers or pickles may be used in place of onions. Serve with egg sauce.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients and bake according to directions on cake mix box.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; add onion, tomato paste and sauces, garlic and oregano.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
In 9 x 13-inch pan layer noodles, meat sauce and cheeses.
Repeat layers.

title: bran gems
directions: Pour boiling water over Bran and let soak.
Cream the Crisco and sugar well; add eggs, one at a time.
Add buttermilk.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add to cream mixture.
Add Bran.
Pour batter into container and cover.
Stores 3 weeks in refrigerator. Use as needed.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° in muffin tins.
Recommend using half the recipe.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine the squash and onion in a saucepan with a small amount of water and boil until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add grated rind and juice of lemon, along with half the cheese, half the bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Stir together.
Pour into 1-quart casserole and top with remaining cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until the top is brown and bubbly.

title: frog legs provencal
directions: Melt butter in a skillet and add tomato sauce, mushrooms, parsley and garlic; simmer for 10 minutes.
Dip frog legs in cream, then in flour.
In other skillet, saute legs in oil for 10 minutes or until brown.
Serve with sauce.
Serves 6.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating each 1 minute.
Add flour, lemon juice and vanilla, beating well. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: spinach pie
directions: Brown sausage and drain; saute chopped onion. Combine sausage and onion with the next 7 ingredients and mix together well. Fill 2 deep dish pie crusts with mixture, evenly. Top each pie with regular pie crust and pinch around edges to seal. Cut a round hole in center of each pie, about the size of a quarter. Combine egg yolk and water and brush on top of pies. Bake at 375° for 1 hour 15 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before slicing. These pies freeze really well. Defrost in refrigerator before baking.

title: easy microwave cheese sauce
directions: Place butter in a 2-cup glass measure. Microwave 45 seconds until melted.
Stir in flour, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Add milk.
Microwave 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes until boiling, stirring a few times after the first minute.
After sauce has cooked and thickened, stir in cheese until melted.
Good on broccoli or baked potatoes.

title: dilly green tomatoes
directions: Break or cut the cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Heat the butter and oil.
Add the chilies, cumin, pepper corns, coriander and ginger.
Fry on medium heat; stir often so the spices don't burn for about a minute.
Add the cauliflower, turmeric and salt. Cook on low heat; turn occasionally until the cauliflower is done, about a half hour.
When you serve, don't scoop up the spices; just spoon out the cauliflower.

title: basic italian meat sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet.
In a large kettle, combine other ingredients.
Drain meat mixture and add to kettle. Bring to a boil.
Turn down to simmer and let cook 2 hours. Do not cover!
Remove from heat.
Use as is for spaghetti.

title: chipped beef-cheese dip
directions: Beat cream cheese with fork until smooth and creamy.
Add chipped beef and mustard; beat well.
Fold in sour cream.
Makes 2 1/3 cups dip.

title: wonderful waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks, then mix with shortening,
honey or sugar and milk.
Mix dry ingredients and liquids enough to just blend them.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Bake according to manufacturer's instructions for your waffle iron.
Makes about 6 large waffles.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, eggs and sugars together.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel, clean and cube potatoes.
Place in medium saucepan and cover with water.
Slice onion and add to water.
Bring to a boil and boil until potatoes are done.
Drain water.
Add butter, milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Thicken to desired consistency with instant potatoes.
Warm milk and enjoy.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a large saucepan cook sugar, syrup and water until the mixture reaches hard ball stage when dropped in a cup of water. Add peanuts and cook until light brown, then add butter and vanilla and stir until well mixed.
Add soda and stir well.
Do not stir too long after adding soda.
(This is the secret of this candy.) Pour into buttered pan.

title: shrimp fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
In a saucepan, melt margarine.
Add milk, then slowly stir Parmesan cheese into milk, stirring constantly with a whisk.
Cook on low heat until sauce becomes slightly thick and creamy.
(Stirring an egg white into the sauce is sometimes beneficial to add thickening.)
Add parsley flakes and mushrooms.
Cook until mushrooms are almost done and add shrimp.
When shrimp are heated through, pour sauce over cooked and drained fettuccine noodles. Toss lightly and serve.

title: abraham lincoln's stewed apples
directions: Peel and core the apples.
Cut in thick slices and saute in the butter, about 3 or 4 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients. Cover and cook slowly until tender.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and slice berries.
Bring sugar, jello, cornstarch and water to boil; boil for 10 minutes and cool.
Place sliced strawberries in cool pie shell.
Pour mixture over berries.
Cool in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: dudley's favorite waist builder
directions: Mix well.
Pour onto wax paper-lined jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown (about 20 to 25 minutes).
While hot, roll up in jelly roll fashion.
When cool, unroll and carefully remove wax paper.
Spread on filling evenly and roll back up.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake as directed (9 x 13 pan). In saucepan, combine 1/2 can of milk and 1 1/2 cups sugar. Bring to rapid boil. Remove from heat and add marshmallows. Stir until melted. Stir in coconut. Pour mixture over cake. In saucepan, combine remaining sugar and remaining milk. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add butter and chocolate chips. Stir until melted. Mix in almonds. Pour over cake. Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: grannie's old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add one egg at a time.
Add flour, milk and 2 teaspoons extract.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 55 minutes.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine refried beans and seasoning mix.
Spread mixture into pan.
Layer remaining ingredients.
Serve with corn chips.

title: tuna turnovers
directions: Drain tuna.
Mix with cream of mushroom soup.
Add green pepper, onion, salt and pepper.
Open refrigerated biscuits.
Pat biscuits into circles.
Spoon tuna filling in center of 10 circles.
Top with remaining circles; pinch edges to seal. Arrange on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until browned.

title: pork chops with peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place oil in the bottom of a large shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper. Arrange in a single layer in a prepared pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes, turning once.
Top chops with peppers, wine and Italian seasoning.
Reduce oven to 325°.
Bake, uncovered, basting occasionally until chops are thoroughly cooked, approximately 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: green sherbet punch
directions: Chill pineapple juice.
Prepare limeade according to directions and mix with pineapple juice. Add sugar, if desired. Add ginger ale.
Spoon sherbet into punch.
Garnish with cherries.

title: crab casserole
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
May put a few buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: curried turkey salad
directions: Combine turkey, celery, mayonnaise, soy sauce, curry, salt and pepper; mix well.
Refrigerate.
Top with pineapple and almonds just before serving.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: easy party punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add next 3 ingredients. Stir in one tray ice cubes until melted.
Spoon in sherbet.
Serve immediately or let stand at room temperature.

title: hot cran-apple cider
directions: Pour juices into large Dutch oven or crock-pot.
Dissolve brown sugar into juices.
Tie spices in cheesecloth and put in cider.
Heat on low heat for 2 hours and remove spices.
Serve hot.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients; store in a jar.
Use 4 teaspoons of tea mix for each cup and add hot water.

title: sweet chicken wings
directions: Marinate chicken wings overnight in a plastic bag, turning occasionally.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Saute onion, garlic and beef in oil.
Add salt and pepper. Layer beef mixture, tomatoes, beans, chili and tortillas in baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake with custard sauce
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar together.
Add egg and mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt and add alternately with buttermilk.
By hand, add vanilla and cut up rhubarb.
Mix well. Put in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup nuts over batter before baking or omit topping and serve with Custard Sauce.

title: beef chowder soup
directions: Cook beef, celery, onion and green pepper.
Add other ingredients and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place chops
on
bottom of casserole. Cover with onions and sprinkle
with
salt.
Pour
uncooked rice over onions and chops. Add tomato soup thinned with water.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.	Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cut chicken in pieces.
Cover with water.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Remove meat from bones and cut into small pieces.
Boil spaghetti in broth for 15 minutes.
Drain (saving broth).
Shred bacon and fry until brown.
Saute onion and pepper in bacon fat.
Add pimentos and mushrooms.
Add to chicken. Combine all with spaghetti and cheese, using broth as needed. Heat through and serve.

title: potato salad(serves 10)
directions: Let potatoes cool, then cut into cubes. Add chopped onions and tomatoes; mix well with salt and parsley. Serve on lettuce leaves with boiled dressing.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Bring 1 2/3 cups of water and 1 tablespoon butter or margarine to a boil.
Add yellow rice.
Mix, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Mix other ingredients and bake in 350° oven until bubbly or 30 minutes, then take out oven and sprinkle with paprika.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine milk and sugar in heavy sauce pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Turn heat low and cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate, karo, butter and vanilla.
Stir until melts and is smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in buttered pan and chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: unbeatable barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and simmer approximately 10 minutes.
Makes enough for 12 pieces of chicken.
Great for fries, too.

title: chicken vegetable stir-fry
directions: Note:
Can use 1 bag frozen Oriental vegetables in place of fresh vegetables.

title: herb chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts in butter.
Salt and pepper.
Place in flat casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes, then uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well and put in buttered 3-quart baking dish. (May be frozen at this time.) Cube 4 slices of day old bread. Toss lightly with melted butter and put on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add soup, chilies, onions and milk.
Cook slowly until onions are tender.
Break into quarters the corn tortillas.
Layer in a casserole first tortilla pieces, cheese and soup mixture until you have used each part three times.
Then top with grated cheese and bake 15 minutes at 300°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water until tender and water has cooked down.
Remove from heat and add egg, 1 cup cheese and margarine.
Mix well; until margarine melts.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle on bread crumbs and 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and put in greased Pyrex dish with crackers and butter on top.
Cook until brown.

title: zucchini goulash
directions: Slice zucchini and onion and saute in olive oil. Slice mushrooms and add to zucchini.

When vegetables are softened add the tomatoes and let simmer until all vegetables are softened and cooked well. (If juice is a little thin, add Wondra to thicken...or cornstarch.) Pour mixture into a casserole dish and cover with cheese. Bake until cheese is melted.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet; saute onion rings until limp and opaque.
Layer half the onions into 1-quart flat baking dish. Cover with half the cheese and half of the crackers.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: toss up cake
directions: Mix 1/4 cup juice from fruit with cream cheese and whipped cream. Layer a large bowl beginning with pound cake (crumpled up), then a layer of cream mixture, then fruit; repeat until bowl is complete.
Top with cream mixture and place in fridge for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: macaroni pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly; drain.
Layer ground beef, macaroni and tomato sauce in 2-quart baking dish.
Pour mixture of water, oregano and garlic salt over layers.
Top with cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with salad and French bread.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: ginger glazed spareribs
directions: Simmer ribs in water until tender.
Drain.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, pepper and ginger in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in lemon juice, soy sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and cook for 3 minutes.
Cover ribs in a shallow pan with sauce and bake for 45 minutes at 400°.
Cover with foil while baking.

title: good-bye carrot casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer half the carrots in the bottom.
Add half of the cheese over top. Then add half the white sauce.
Repeat. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly and browned.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sift flour and salt together.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Mix well 1/2 cup flour with mixture.
Toss to coat evenly; set aside.

title: pasta and broccoli
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender, but not brown. Add broccoli, water and bouillon.
Bring to boil.
Stir in pasta. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in parsley, salt and pepper.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: applesauce cookies(diet)
directions: Cream the margarine with sugar substitute.
Combine soda and applesauce; add to margarine mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; stir just until blended.
Pour into nonstick 7 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs until frothy. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole. Bake in preheated 350° oven 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 4 servings.

title: french burgers
directions: Mix hamburger, ketchup, garlic salt and pepper.
Spread on bread.
Slice into 6-inch pieces.
Top with onion and cheese. Place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Mix cheese and broccoli together.
Place in a souffle dish.

title: swedish apple bread pudding
directions: Place bread slices in a single layer in a shallow pan.
Evenly drizzle 1/2 cup of half and half over bread.
In a medium saucepan mix sugar and water.
Bring to boiling.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Return to medium heat.
Add about a third of the apple slices and simmer each portion 3 minutes.
Remove with a slotted spoon.
Reserve sugar syrup.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream oleo and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients, Sucaryl and milk.
Chill dough for 20 minutes.
Form small balls.
Bake at 350° until brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 24 cookies or less.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 stick margarine (softened) and 1 egg. Pat into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Beat together the cream cheese (softened), 3 eggs, lemon juice, 1 stick margarine and powdered sugar (reserve 4 tablespoons of powdered sugar to sprinkle on top of cooled squares).
Pour cream cheese mixture over cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (until edges brown). Cool, then cut into squares.

title: easy microwave fudge
directions: In 4-quart bowl, microwave margarine on High 1 minute or until melted.
Add sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Microwave 5 minute or until mixture begins to boil, stirring after 3 minutes.
Continue microwaving 5 1/2 minutes more, stirring after 3 minutes, scraping bowl and mixing well.
Gradually stir in chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 9-inch or 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares after completely cooled.

title: apple crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Peel apples; arrange in greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with white sugar.
Combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Spread over apples and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in
stick
butter;
put in a big bowl. Add all
ingredients
except
cheese and broccoli.
Stir well. Add 3/4 cup
cheese
(reserve
1/4 cup for topping) and cooked broccoli. Place in
8 x 13-inch slightly greased baking dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese
over the top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix parsley, thyme, salt, pepper, garlic and lemon juice.
Pour half over the chicken.
Bake 20 minutes.
Turn chicken over and pour remaining liquid over chicken.
Bake another 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Serve over rice.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar
and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add
flavoring
and color.
Bake in three 9-inch layer pans
at
for 30 minutes.
You may add 2 teaspoons cocoa to flour if you wish.

title: hjortetakk
directions: You will also need a deep saucepan or automatic deep fryer.

title: chicken dorito casserole
directions: Pour Doritos into casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Mix the soup, sour cream and milk together, then pour over chicken and chips.
Grate cheese over top and bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: brownies
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt chocolate and margarine.
Add sugar and cool.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan (greased and floured).
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: miniature meatballs
directions: Mix meat and the next 8 ingredients; shape into 1-inch balls. Pour 2 tablespoons oil into large skillet; brown meatballs. Remove from skillet.
Pour off fat.
Heat chili sauce and grape jelly in pan until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs; stir until coated.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Makes about 20 meatballs.

title: fresh salmon pate
directions: Bake salmon in a little water with lemon.
When cooled, flake salmon into bowl, removing all bones and skin.
Add butter, sour cream and onion to salmon.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a mold (a bowl will do), lined with wax paper.
Chill overnight.

title: microwave hawaiian chicken
directions: Remove skin and bone from breasts; arrange in 1 1/2-quart microproof casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients; blend well. Pour over chicken.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 10 minutes.
Rearrange chicken.
Cover.
Cook on High 10 to 12 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes enough for 2 to 4 people.
Total cooking time: 20 to 22 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a skillet cook the sausage until browned.
Drain well.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the cheese, chicken soup, sour cream, french onion dip, chopped onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper. Fold in thawed hash brown potatoes. Mix well.
Spread 1/2 half of the browned sausage over hash brown mixture.
Repeat second layer 1/2 of hash brown mixture.
Top with remaining sausage.
Bake at 350 degrees for about one hour or until casserole is golden brown.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix well and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Add marshmallows if desired and brown.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown meat, onion and garlic salt.
Stir in flour, add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer
minutes.
Add soup and mushrooms and simmer 15 more
minutes.
Fold
in sour cream and heat only until warm.
Serve over rice.

title: microwave sweet-sour meatballs
directions: Combine onion, salt, tomato soup, lemon juice and brown sugar in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook on High 4 to 5 1/2 minutes or until simmering.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Roll beef into 1-inch balls.
Place balls in mixture and spoon some sauce over meatballs.
Cook on High 7 1/2 to 9 3/4 minutes or until meat is cooked through.
Stir in pineapple.
Heat on High for 1 minute and 20 seconds.
As appetizer, serve with toothpicks.
As main dish, serve over rice.

title: salmon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and beat with mixer until smooth.
Refrigerate until firm, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, flour and jello; then add eggs, oil, water and 3/4 cup strawberries.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° (30 to 40 minutes for a 9 x 13-inch pan, 25 to 35 minutes for two 9-inch pans). Cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over browned meat and simmer at 325°.

title: calico beans(easy baked beans)
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon (not the pieces) and onion.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
I sometimes add a can of B & M Beans also.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix together flour, sugar, milk and baking powder and pour into casserole. Spoon in pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no-mix dessert
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour undrained pineapple into pan and spread.
Add pie filling in an even layer.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top; scatter chopped nuts over mix.
Cut butter into patties and place on top.
Don't mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until brown.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: parmesan onion canapes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Spread on toast.
Place on baking sheets.
Broil 4 inches from source of heat 2 to 3 minutes or until golden and bubbly.
Makes 36.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, melted margarine and egg well with a spoon. Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Put mixture into pan and pat down with hand.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs together. Pour over cake mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sour milk doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together; add lemon rind and melted shortening, then milk alternately with sifted dry ingredients, adding a little more flour if necessary to make dough just stiff enough to handle easily.
Turn onto floured board; pat or roll 3/4-inch thick and cut into doughnuts.
Cook in deep hot fat. Drain on unglazed paper and when cool, roll in powdered sugar. Makes about three dozen doughnuts.

title: peanut butter sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, combine sweetened condensed milk and peanut butter.
Cook and stir until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve with ice cream.

title: rainbow salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Let cool completely. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Will keep several days, covered, in refrigerator.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Mix shortening, salt and sugar.
Add boiling water.
Let cool.
Add yeast, beaten egg and flour.
Grease bowl with shortening.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick and sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon mixture (you can add raisins and nuts at this point).
Roll and cut 3/4 inch thick.
Grease baking pan.
Place roll in pan and let rise until double in size (about 1 hour).
Makes 12 large rolls.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar.
Dough can be stored in refrigerator overnight and rolled out the next day.

title: gouda chutney dip
directions: Take cheese out of shell carefully.
Save shell to serve dip in.
Beat all ingredients in food processor.
Pile back in shell. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix and knead and let rise in greased covered bowl until double.
Punch down and make 3 loaves and let rise.
Then bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Brush tops with butter.
Wrap in foil.

title: sonny's favorite fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add after mixing together the flour, baking powder and salt; mix.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Coat fruit with small amount of flour; add to mixture.
Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Bake for 3 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: chicken rice dinner
directions: Brown
chicken with margarine in pan, turning until all sides are brown.	Sprinkle parsley, basil and salt on chicken. Spoon the
soup
into
the pan and add 2 cans of water.
Stir soup
and water
until mixed.
Add bouillon cubes and cook 20 minutes.
Add diced
carrots
and
the
rice; cook another 20 minutes on medium.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring tea bags and whole
spice to a boil in 1 quart of water. Let stand	until
lukewarm.
Take	out bags and spice; add sugar. Pour
in gallon container and add vinegar, pineapple juice and orange juice.
Serve hot.

title: smoky corn chowder
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in sausage links, corn and lima beans.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together softened margarine and confectioners sugar and peanut butter.
When mixture looks like cornmeal, form into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Chill 2 to 4 hours on a cookie sheet. Melt paraffin in top of double boiler, add semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Drop 1 ball at a time using toothpicks into hot chocolate mixture.
Take out and let drain on waxed paper.
It will harden almost immediately.
Store in a tin box in the refrigerator.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: mystery fruit cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool and crumble into large pan.
Add fruit and nuts to crumbled cake.
Make up fluffy white frosting mix.
Mix with cake, fruits and nuts.
Pack firmly into foil lined loaf pans.
Cover with foil and chill in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Can be frozen or kept in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour venison
directions: Melt butter in frypan; add onion and simmer until onion is transparent.
Add venison; cook until browned.
Place mixture into crock-pot.
Add ketchup, brown sugar and green pepper.
Cook on high for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve on bed of rice.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and chill.
A child's favorite. Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with 1/2 pastry rolled to 1/8-inch thickness, allowing 1-inch overhang.
In a large bowl, stir together sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon. Toss with apple slices and lemon juice until coated. Turn into pie plate.
Dot with margarine. Roll remaining pastry to 12-inch circle.
Make several slits to permit steam to escape.
Cover pie with pastry. Seal and flute edge.
Bake in a 425° oven for 50 minutes or until crust is golden and apples are tender.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: sugar cookies
directions: First, mix top 3 ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients, gradually adding milk.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 minutes.

title: bierock casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Add cabbage to mixture and steam.
Add cream of mushroom soup to mixture and continue steaming until ingredients have cooked through.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 can of crescent rolls.
Top rolls with hamburger mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and top cheese with second can of crescent rolls.
Pinch this layer of rolls together. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Casserole may be frozen.

title: lemon lush cake
directions: Mix the first three ingredients and spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes in a preheated oven at 350°. Mix next four ingredients and spread on cooled crust.
Mix instant pudding and milk; spread over previous mixture.
Cover with remainder of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts if you prefer.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Rinse beef to remove salty taste.
Chop or slice into small strips.
Mix all ingredients.
Form into ball and chill.
Good when served in hollowed out green pepper.

title: spinach pie
directions: Line lightly greased pie plate with slices of Muenster cheese. Mix remaining ingredients and fill plate. Put remaining cheese on top as crust.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or until lightly browned.

title: igloo
directions: Cut apple in half; trim out core.
Place apple, cut side down on a plate.
Spread smooth peanut butter all over top of apple half.
Place small white marshmallows on peanut butter until apple half looks like an igloo.

title: christmas in snow cake
directions: Soft gelatin in cold water.
Adding boiling water, stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple (including juice). Chill until partly firm.
Whip, according to package directions, the whipped topping (2 packages); fold into gelatin mixture. Remove all brown from angel food cake and slice into thin slices. Place in bottom of cake pan.
Alternate layers of cake and gelatin; add third package of Dream Whip mixture on top of cake.
Sprinkle coconut on top, then place cherries around the top.

title: pan rolls(easy-tasty-healthy)
directions: Note:
1/4 cup sugar can be used instead of the honey.

title: almond joys
directions: Mix margarine and condensed milk. Add 2 tablespoons of flour, powdered sugar and coconut.
Chill mixture.
Shape into balls. Press 1 toasted almond on top.
Roll in melted chocolate.
Place on waxed paper until set.

title: tomato medley
directions: Cut into pieces (as for soup) the first 3 ingredients.
Add a little salt.
Simmer in the juice of the tomatoes.
Add water sparingly to cover until tender.
Add cut up tomatoes and green beans.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons margarine.
Simmer, adding one tablespoon cornstarch, dissolved in water to thicken.

title: catalina baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Scrub potatoes and slice lengthwise into spears. In a shallow dish, pour dressing in and coat each potato slice.
Spread out on a greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle garlic and parsley over potatoes. Bake 20 minutes or until crispy.

title: diabetic baked apples
directions: Wash and core apples. Pare a strip from the top of each apple. Place in baking pan. Put a tablespoon of raisins in each apple. Pour apple juice over apples. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until tender. Baste with juice twice while baking.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Put spareribs in shallow baking pan.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Pour off drippings.

title: eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant as for frying. Dip in beaten egg and cracker crumbs. Fry the slices. Make stacks, alternating eggplant, undiluted tomato soup and grated cheese, using 3 slices of eggplant to each stack. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: miniature nut filled pastries
directions: Measure flour into large bowl.
Add margarine and cut in with pastry blender or 2 knives until coarse crumbs form.
Stir in egg yolks and sour cream until dough is well mixed.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth.
Chill dough 20 minutes.

title: nutmeg cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together three times.
Cream butter, add sugar gradually, cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Beat until smooth after each addition, add flavoring.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 375° for about 45 minutes.
When cooled, sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat eggs very light and add the sour cream.
Mix all together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican layered salad
directions: Use 9 or 10-inch casserole dish.
For first layer, spread jalapeno bean dip.
For second layer, mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco mix.
Mix and spread over bean dip.
For third layer, add grated Cheddar cheese.
For fourth layer, cut up tomatoes over other layer.
For fifth layer, sprinkle chopped green onions all over.
Chill and serve with corn chips.

title: apricot bavarian
directions: Mix Jell-O and sugar.
Add boiling water; mix well.
Add cold water.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until the consistency of egg whites.
Remove from refrigerator and beat with hand mixer.
Remove to another bowl.
Beat Dream Whip as directed.
Add to Jell-O.
Beat again with mixer.
Put in mold or bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: children's trail mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a container with a tight lid.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in a saucepan.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Pour over popped corn in a kettle.
Toss to coat evenly.
Cook slowly, stirring, 5 minutes more or until sticky.
Shape into balls with greased hands.

title: fluffy meringue
directions: Beat egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add the sugar, beating until all sugar is dissolved and peaks are stiff and glossy.
Carefully spread the meringue over hot, cooked filling, being careful to seal the meringue to edge of pie crust all the way around.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue peaks are golden.

title: pink salad
directions: Heat pineapple until boiling; stir in jello until dissolved. (Do not use any water.)
Let cool.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Cook noodles according to pkg. directions.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce,
mushrooms and Italian seasoning.
Drain noodles.
In a 5 qt. slow cooker coated with nonstick cooking spray, spread a third of the meat sauce. Cover with a third of the noodles and pepperoni.
Sprinkle with a third of the cheeses.
Repeat layers twice.
Cover and cook on low for 3-4 hours or until heated through and cheese is melted. Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until stiff.
Add pecans, stirring to coat thoroughly.
Combine last 3 ingredients and add to pecan mixture.
Mix well.
Place on buttered cookie sheet and bake at 225° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana nuggets
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
Sift flour with soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix into the egg mixture. Add the mashed bananas and rolled oats, mixing well.
Stir in the chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot apple surprise
directions: Brush tortillas on both sides with melted butter.
Heat 4 at a time in a microwave for 25 seconds each.
Combine apples, raisins and walnuts.
Fill tortillas with equal amounts of apple mixture and fold burrito style.
Place seam side down in shallow baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Turn tortillas over; bake an additional 10 minutes or until crisp. Serve hot with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: macaroni-cheese salad
directions: Combine macaroni, ham, cheese, celery, green pepper, pickle relish, pimentos and onion in bowl.
Blend together mayonnaise, mustard and salt.
Add to macaroni mixture and toss.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and place in bowl.

title: buttermilk pie crust dough
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Add butter and shortening.
Cut in, using hands or pastry blender, until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk and stir with fork until moist clumps form.
(Dough can also be prepared in processor. Using on/off turns, cut butter and shortening into dry ingredients until coarse meal forms.
Add buttermilk and process until moist clumps form.)

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into balls.
Bake in 400° oven about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and egg.
Add pineapple.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder. Add dry ingredients, walnuts and vanilla to first mixture.
Mix well. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake in moderately hot 425° oven for 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chess pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix the meal and flour. Put this in sugar and stir up. Add the lemon juice and vanilla. Pour in unbaked pie crusts and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first three ingredients until creamy.
Beat in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Cover; chill about 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with tines of fork dipped in granulated sugar to form crisscross pattern.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Store tightly covered.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Grease baking sheet. Sift dry ingredients into a bowl. Cut in shortening. Beat egg lightly and add milk. Combine dry and liquid ingredients together. Mix with fork until dough holds its shape. Turn out on floured board and knead lightly. Roll about 3/4 inch thick. Cut into biscuits and bake 12 minutes.

title: date-nut balls
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and dates.
Cook 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal, nuts and coconut. Roll into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
(Putting several balls in Ziploc bag with powdered sugar and shaking saves a lot of time.)

title: macaroni loaf
directions: Place layer of cooked macaroni into a greased baking dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs, grated cheese, parsley, onion, salt and butter between each layer.
Repeat until all ingredients are used. Pour egg and milk over mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Drop marshmallows in jello, stirring until well dissolved; let cool.
Add lemon juice and mayonnaise to cream cheese.
Combine with jello mixture.
Add pineapple and nuts; chill.

title: quick broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt; drain well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated.
Yields 4 cups.

title: fruit cobbler without crust
directions: Melt margarine in square baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk together.
Stir and mix well.
Pour into melted margarine; do not stir.
Pour 2 cups fruit juice of choice over mixture.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325° in oven.

title: gold band mint julep
directions: Place mint leaves, sugar and 1 ounce of bourbon in a tumbler. Stir gently with spoon. Add scoop of ice and stir vigorously. Add ice to 1-inch from top. Add equal parts of bourbon and water to fill glass. Place sprig of fresh mint on top. Zest with twist of lemon and dust with powdered sugar. Enjoy!

title: low-fat basic vegetable rice
directions: Cook rice, using chicken stock.
Cook rice 15 minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crush cookies until fine.
Melt butter and mix with cookies. Reserve 1 cup cookie mixture, then pat remaining mixture into a 9 x 12-inch cake pan. Spoon in softened ice cream.
Spoon on whipped topping and drizzle with syrup.
Sprinkle with cookie crumbs and nuts.
Keep in freezer.
Cut into bars.

title: lemon broccoli
directions: Divide broccoli into florets and stalks.
Remove woody stems. Steam broccoli until tender, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add the onion, celery and garlic.
Cook until onion begins to brown.
Remove from heat.
Add broccoli, lemon juice, peel, salt and pepper.
Mix well and serve.
Serves eight 3/4 cup servings with 58 calories, 4 g fat and 0 mg cholesterol per serving.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown meat.
Add tomato sauce and envelope of sauce mix. Simmer.
Layer into 9 x 13-inch pan the meat mixture on bottom, layer of cheeses and any other ingredients such as pepperoni, green pepper, etc.
Put sour cream on top, then put rolls with butter and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 370° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot dog chili sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain grease.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: dilled carrot bundles
directions: Cut carrots into 3-inch julienne strips.
Arrange carrots on a steaming rack and place over boiling water; cover and steam 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove carrots and plunge them into ice water to stop the cooking process; drain.
Separate carrots into 8 bundles.
Place leek strips in boiling water for 1 minute; drain.
Carefully tie a leek strip around each carrot bundle and set aside.
Combine butter, dill and salt and pepper in a Dutch oven and heat until butter is melted.
Carefully add carrot bundles and cook over medium heat until heated through, spooning butter over carrots frequently.

title: yogurt and lemon ice
directions: Pour the yogurt, soft cheese and sugar into a bowl and beat until the sugar is fully dissolved. Thoroughly mix in the lemon or lime juice and rind. Pour into the ice cream maker and proceed as directed by your machine.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; add beaten egg yolks and milk.
Beat thoroughly.
Add shortening.
Mix in beaten egg whites.
Bake on hot waffle iron until golden brown.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients until soft.
You can add food coloring of your choice.
Store in Ziploc bag.

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: With sharp knife slice across width of chicken breasts to make very thin pieces.
In medium bowl mix chicken, cornstarch, sherry, ginger and 1 teaspoon salt; set aside.
In 12-inch skillet or 5-quart saucepan over medium-high heat in salad oil, cook walnuts about 3 minutes until lightly browned, stirring constantly with slotted spoon.
Spoon walnuts onto paper towels to drain.
In hot oil in skillet, stir-fry (stirring quickly and often) mushrooms, bamboo shoots, Chinese pea pods and 1/4 teaspoon salt until pea pods are tender-crisp, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Spoon vegetables into medium bowl, leaving oil in skillet.
Stir-fry chicken in the oil about 5 minutes.
Stir in vegetables.
Place on warm platter; sprinkle with walnuts.
Serve.

title: rainbow veggie tray
directions: Place each of the first 3 ingredients separately into zip-top plastic bags; set aside.
Combine vinegar and next 6 ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Pour marinade equally over vegetables in plastic bags; seal securely and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: herbed sour cream bread
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, sugar, salt, yeast, sour cream, butter, herbs and water in a large bowl. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed. Stir in the rest of the flour to make a soft dough. Cover and let rise for 35 minutes.
Stir down and divide into two well-greased casseroles.
Cover and let rise 50 minutes. Bake at 375° until done, or about 35 minutes.

title: blueberry banana bread
directions: Toss berries with 2 tablespoons flour.
Sift remaining flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cream butter or margarine; gradually beat in sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixture and bananas alternately, in three parts.
Stir in blueberries.
Bake in greased bread loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 65 minutes.

title: holiday surprise
directions: Place pineapple with juice in a large bowl.
Add pudding mix and blend thoroughly.
Fold in whipped topping, marshmallows and pecans.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: pepperoni pizza salad(must be refrigerated for several hours before serving.)
directions: In large bowl combine the tomatoes, green peppers, cheese, pepperoni, olives, and onion.
In a small bowl combine the tomato juice, vinegar, oil, garlic, basil and pepper; mix well. Pour tomato mixture over and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Just before serving sprinkle with croutons.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Season with Tony Chachere Creole seasoning. Bake at 350° until done.

title: spinach feta rice
directions: Combine rice, broth and water in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil and stir.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Cook onion, mushrooms and garlic in large skillet, coated with cooking spray until onion is tender.
Stir in lemon juice and oregano.
Add spinach, cheese and pepper to rice.
Toss lightly until spinach is wilted.
Serves 4.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Stir in egg and flavoring; knead until soft dough is formed.
(The more you knead, the better.)
Shape into balls about walnut-size.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten slightly with hand.
Dip blunt end of chopstick into red coloring; make a dent about 1/4-inch deep in center of cookies, or press an almond into the center.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until tender; drain.
Mash potatoes until smooth, adding remaining ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.
Cool.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
(Will keep well for a week.)

title: marinated green salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Marinate in tightly covered bowl in refrigerator for at least 10 hours.
Toss just before serving.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/4 cups of boiling water; add sugar and crushed pineapple.
Set aside.
In blender, chop fresh cranberries in the orange juice (half at a time), then add to Jell-O mixture. Add nuts and place in large bowl or casserole dish.
(Makes 2 quarts so requires a rather large bowl or casserole dish.)

title: pineapple nut cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and pineapple. Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add nut meats.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned (about 12 minutes at 350°).
Makes 4 dozen.

title: baked porks
directions: Season the pork chops with Season-All.
Place the chops in a skillet and brown on both sides.
Place the chops in a baking dish.
Add soup, hash browns and sour cream.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Five minutes before removing from oven, add the cheese and onion rings.

title: poor man cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; cook for 2 minutes.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with vanilla frosting glaze.

title: taco dip
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Mix in salsa until smooth.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: tasty baked ham
directions: Rinse ham good.
Place in baking pan.
Mix brown sugar and orange juice to a thick consistency.
Spread over entire ham. Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours.
Do not turn ham over.
Drain juices and serve.
This is great.
You must try it!

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and nutmeg. Add melted oleo.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell; bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 13 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and pat in bottom of baking dish.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: mustard potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes 20 minutes and drain. Boil eggs.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add potatoes to mix.
Chop boiled eggs. Add eggs and onion.
Mix gently.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: honey-lime dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in small saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.

title: tomato relish
directions: Peel and finely chop tomatoes.
Finely chop onions, bell peppers and hot peppers.
Mix all ingredients and simmer 2 hours. Put in sterilized canning jars.

title: italian rice
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, saute garlic in oil for 1 minute. Stir in spinach. Cover and cook for 3 - 4 minutes or until tender; drain well. Add the vinegar, salt and pepper. Stir in the rice and red peppers until combined. Cook and stir until heated through.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup catsup.
Press in an 8 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch square pan.
Spread 1/4 cup catsup on top.
Place in oven and bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let set about 15 minutes before serving.

title: jello salad
directions: Use a glass bowl the size of salad you want to make.
The glass bowl lets the layers show through.
Start with a good layer of torn bite size lettuce.
Layer of tomatoes, defrosted frozen peas, sliced mushrooms, sliced hard-cooked eggs, grated American cheese and a layer of mayonnaise to cover all.
Chop cooked and drained bacon, and sprinkle over the top or use bacon bits.
This is best made the night before and covered with plastic wrap.
(For those that like onions, I use a light layer of green onions in mine.)

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine all in electric blender on low speed for 3 minutes. Pour into a 9 1/2-inch deep dish pie pan, preferably glass.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes its own crust.
Serve warm or cold.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook unpeeled sweet potatoes until tender.
Remove jackets. Place marshmallows in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish, sprayed with Pam.
Slice cooked potatoes thinly and place over marshmallows. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
