Cut up 1 stick of margarine and place on top.
Bake in slow oven at 225° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jodi's casserole
directions: It's just a matter of layering these ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan:

1 package crescent rolls, browned hamburger, olives, mushrooms, spaghetti sauce, thin slices of cheese and the other package of crescent rolls. Bake at 350° until the rolls are golden brown, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: stuffed onions
directions: Peel onions; cook in boiling salted water for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut a slice off the top.
Scoop out insides; chop and set aside.
Mix sausage and Worcestershire sauce.
Brown meat mixture until it is no longer pink.
Drain and cool.
Stuff onions with meat mixture.
Combine chopped onions and tomato sauce; pour over onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and spinach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with a sweet and sour salad dressing.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars in 2 cups sweet milk in double boiler.
Let cool.
Mix eggs and sugar.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and Carnation milk, then add Milky Way mixture and mix well.
Pour into 1 gallon freezer and add enough milk to fill container within 2-inches of top.
Mix well and freeze.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: steak or chicken parmesan
directions: Tenderize meat.
Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Dip pieces of meat into eggs, then in crumbs.
Brown on both sides in heated oil in skillet.
Remove to baking dish.
Pour oil from skillet, leaving any pieces of meat, etc.
Stir in tomato sauce, garlic, butter, sugar and Italian seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over meat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake covered 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: cornbread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, oil, corn, peppers, onion, cornmeal and one cup of cheese.
Pour into a well-greased baking dish or iron skillet that is piping hot.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins, water and dates 20 minutes slowly (simmer).
Add sugar, cold water and shortening.
Let this mixture get cool.
Then add baking soda, cinnamon, flour, salt and cloves.
Mix well.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kahlua dessert
directions: Bake cake according to package directions on box.
Cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix pudding, milk and Kahlua together. Layer into large bowl half the cake cubes, half the pudding mixture.
Top with half of the Cool Whip and half of the crushed candy Heath bars.
Then repeat the layers.
Looks very pretty in a large glass clear bowl.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Gradually stir into creamed mixture.
Chill dough 2 hours or more.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll each ball in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.
(Cookies should be lightly browned, but still soft.)
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: pineapple slaw
directions: Stir yogurt; spoon onto several layers of heavy-duty paper towels and spread to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cover with paper towels; let stand 5 minutes.
Scrape into a bowl, using a rubber spatula; stir in mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Combine cabbage and pineapple in a bowl; toss well.
Add yogurt mixture, tossing gently to coat. Cover and chill.
Garnish with pineapple, if desired.
Yield:
4 (1 cup) servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Add all ingredients together and beat.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350° in 9-inch pie shell.

title: vegetables
directions: Saute onions in oil for 1 minute.
Add cucumbers; cook another minute.
Remove vegetables from pan.
Combine soy sauce, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick.
Serve over spareribs.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix crackers and margarine.
Spread half in casserole dish. Mix all other ingredients and spread in dish.
Spread remaining cracker mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: overnight salad
directions: Chop lettuce, celery, green peppers and green onions.
Layer each vegetable in a large glass bowl.
Spread 1 cup mayonnaise on top.
Sprinkle 2 teaspoons sugar over this.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Cook bacon crisp (2 to 3 slices), crumble and sprinkle on top.
Cover dish with foil.
Leave overnight in refrigerator.

title: 7 layer dinner
directions: Layer ingredients; end with hamburg as top layer.
Pour tomato juice over top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in double boiler or microwave.
Add peanut butter; mix, and remove from stove.
Stir in marshmallows and noodles.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Chill until hard.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add vanilla.
Add eggs; beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter, then add sifted ingredients. Form into tiny balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork dipped in water; crisscross.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini delight
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place melted butter or margarine in pan.
Arrange zucchini in one layer using all of the zucchini. Next, layer peppers; next layer onions.
Mix cooking oil and tomato sauce and pour over all.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and Mozzarella cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at least 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until done, but not mushy.
Peel when cold, then grate or shred into long 9x13 buttered dish.

title: orange glazed cornish hens
directions: Tie legs of each hen together; turn wing tips under backs. Place on a greased rack in a roasting pan.
Brush with butter; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 1 hour. In a saucepan, combine the remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Spoon over hens. Bake 15 minutes longer or until a meat thermometer reads 180°.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Remove the crust from the bread and set aside.
Arrange bread slices in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with chicken.
Cover with the mushrooms and chestnuts.

title: chocolate peanut butter no-bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Enjoy!

title: lemon schaum torte
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar until soft peaks form. Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, on high speed until stiff glossy peaks form and sugar is dissolved. Spread meringue on the bottom and up the sides of a greased 13x9 pan. Bake at 275 degrees for one hour. Turn oven off and let stand in oven for one hour. Do not open door. Remove from the oven; cool on a wire rack. In the top of a double boiler, combine the egg yolks and remaining sugar. Gradually stir in lemon juice and peel. Cook and stir over simmering water for 15 minutes or until mixture is thickened and reaches 160 degrees. Cover and refrigerate until cool. In a mixing bowl, beat the cream and confectioners' sugar until stiff peaks form. Spread half over meringue; cover with the lemon mixture. Top with remaining cream mixture. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat; add soup and vegetables. Pour into casserole. Mix corn bread according to directions on package. Pour batter over meat mixture and bake until bread is cooked and browned.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients well except chicken.
Put chicken in pan. Pour sauce over, covering pieces.
Cover with aluminum foil and cook in a 300° oven for 3 hours.
Serve with rice, rice pilaf or mashed potatoes.
Use sauce as gravy.
Delicious!

title: drizzle
directions: Mix well and drizzle over any cake.
Flavoring can be changed and food coloring added to suit cake.

title: chocolate cake of mrs. cushman brown
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream together well. Add chocolate and vanilla; blend.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour which has been sifted with soda and cream of tartar, alternately with milk, beating after each addition until smooth.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan (greased and floured) in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients.
Add vanilla, flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and orange juice.
Add apples and nuts or raisins.
Beat everything together.
Batter is thicker than regular cake.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1hour.

title: oatmeal cake and icing
directions: Mix together oats and boiling water and let stand in bowl. Blend all ingredients (including oats and water) together and pour in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (check though, ovens vary); it may take only 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Drain off pineapple juice and stir into egg yolks, sugar, flour and water.
Cook until thick; let cool.

title: herb rolls
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in 9-inch pie pan.
Let melt.
Blend well.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Swish each one in melted mixture.
Arrange pieces (touching) in pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand short time to absorb butter and herbs.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix and bake in a deep dish unbaked pie shell 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine onion with other items, except cheese, and mix well. Pour into a well-greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake until cheese is melted. Serves 4.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: hot rolls
directions: Scald milk and pour over sugar and shortening.
Add mashed potatoes and when all has cooled to lukewarm, add yeast, which has been dissolved in warm milk.
Add 5 cups flour.
Let rise until double in bulk (about 2 hours).
Then add salt, soda and baking powder to remaining flour and make a light dough.
Grease large bowl and put dough in it.
Put in refrigerator.
When ready to use, roll into your favorite shapes and allow to rise in warm room. Bake at 425° to 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Combine cheese and oleo; blend well.
Spread on ham.
Roll up and chill several hours.
Slice in about 3 1/2 dozen slices. Place on round Ritz crackers.
Let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes before serving.

title: date nut cake
directions: Pour water over dates; stir in baking soda and set aside to cool.
Sift together flour and salt.
Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Add
eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately
with
date mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: basic cookie recipe
directions: Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: lattice top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup onions.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 20 minutes covered.
Cut crescent rolls into 6 strips and form into lattice over mixture.
Bake 15 minutes longer uncovered.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake an additional 3 to 5 minutes.

title: quick and easy baked bean dinner
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add green pepper and onion to 12 x 18-inch microwave dish.
Cover; microwave on High 3 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, combine brown sugar and mustard.
Stir in beans and pineapple.
Add to green pepper mixture.
Stir to combine. Microwave uncovered on High 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Serve with polish sausage or hot dogs.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper and coat with flour. Heat oil in a frying pan.
Add chops.
Saute for 3 minutes on each side.
Add onions and saute for another 5 minutes, turning chops once.
Pour in beer and beef broth.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove chops and place on a preheated platter.
Season sauce to taste.
Blend cornstarch with a small amount of cold water.
Stir into sauce and cover until thick and bubbly.
Pour over pork chops.

title: lokse
directions: Place 1/2 cup of cubed hoagies as the bottom layer in a glass bowl. Place 1/2 cup of ground poppy seeds on top of this layer. Place 1/3 cup of powdered sugar as the third layer. Add a little bit of boiling water on this layer just enough to moisten the hoagies. Repeat the layering 3 times. Press down on the final layer gently after adding the boiling water. Let cool, serve chilled.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add remaining ingredients. Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: irish potato cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together. In a separate bowl, mix flour, cocoa, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves. Mix all together. Last, fold in raisins and nuts. Bake in cake pans at 300° for 25 minutes or until done. Let layers cool. (Makes 4 layers.)

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Cut together first 6 ingredients.
Add 2/3 cup milk mixed with 1 egg.
Knead on well-floured surface until smooth.
Pat out for 6 biscuits (inch or so thick).
Make 3 more biscuits.
Put in ungreased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mustard potato salad
directions: After boiling potatoes and cooling, pour Italian dressing over.
Add onion and green pepper.

title: mocha bourbon mud cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Butter and flour a 10 inch springform pan or Bundt pan.
Melt chocolate in top pan of a double boiler over gently simmering water or in a microwave; set aside.
In a small cup, dissolve espresso powder in 1/4 cup boiling water.
In a medium size bowl, whisk together flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl of electric mixer, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla. On low speed, beat in 1/3 of flour mixture.
Beat in espresso, then beat in bourbon.
Beat in 1/2 of remaining flour mixture with 1 cup water, then beat in the rest of flour mixture.
Pour batter into prepared pan, and smooth top.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes, until top is slightly puffy and a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool completely in pan on a wire rack.
To serve, run a sharp knife around side of springform pan.
Remove side of pan and transfer cake to a serving platter.
Cake will keep, covered at room temperature, for several days.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, cut into slices and serve with whipped cream. Makes 10 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash in big bowl and add all the other things together. Pour into a big baking dish or pan.
Mix 1/2 cup grated cheese and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs in bowl and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chip and nut cake
directions: Remove a spoon or two of cake mix.
Coat chocolate chips and nuts; set aside.
Combine cake mix, eggs, oil, water, vanilla, pudding mix and sour cream.
Mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Pour 1/2 cup of granulated sugar into the blender and cover. Process at high for 60 to 70 seconds.
Let stand for 30 seconds with the lid on, until the sugar settles.
Rest the motor 2 minutes before repeating.
This will make about 2/3 cup of powdered sugar.

title: crunchy cabbage slaw
directions: Remove flavor packet from soup mix and reserve.
Break noodles into pieces and place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Add sliced almonds.
Bake at 350°, stirring occasionally, 5-10 minutes or until toasted.
Set aside.
Whisk together reserved flavor packet, oil, vinegar, and sugar in a bowl until blended. Chill 1 hour.
Toss together cabbage, carrot, onions, and dressing in a large bowl.
Place noodles around outside edge of cabbage mixture and top with almonds.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice.
Chill, then add celery, onions, lettuce, peas, almonds, water chestnuts and salmon, chicken, ham or shrimp.

title: chicken and grape salad
directions: Combine chicken, lemon juice, celery, grapes and seasonings. Toss lightly with mayonnaise and sour cream.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Garnish each salad with 4 pecan halves and 2 pimento strips.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend until coarse; add 1/4 cup ice water and mix.
Roll out for two 9-inch crusts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Peel shrimp; keep peelings to make stock. Add water, whole onion, whole stalk of celery, and simmer for 1/2 hour. Strain broth. Puree corn and whipping cream; add to broth. Then add butter, seasonings & simmer. Add seafood & continue cooking for 5 minutes or until shrimp is pink.

title: guacamole
directions: Chop very fine green chiles, onion, and tomato. Next cut in little pieces of avocado. Add lemon juice and salt. Combine chili mixture with avocado.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel the black skin of the eggplant and slice it into about 1/2-inch slices.
Heat the oil in a nonstick pan over medium-high heat.
Fry the eggplant until it becomes blond-light brown color. Place over napkins to drain excess oil.
Place the tomatoes in boiling water for 20 seconds, then cool over cold water and peel the skin.
Slice into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices.
Brown the meats with the chopped onion in a skillet.
Add the spices with the salt after cooking.
Very lightly brown pine nuts 45 seconds over high heat in frying pan.
Mix the meat (cooked) with the pine nuts.
In a medium or large casserole, put one layer of sliced tomatoes, one layer meat.

On top of the tomatoes, spread 1 cup tomato sauce over the meat, place another layer of eggplant, another layer of meat, another layer of sliced tomatoes and finally, sprinkle 1 cup of tomato sauce over the whole casserole.
Bake in the oven (uncovered) for 30 minutes at 350°.
May be presented hot with rice or Arabic bread.

title: green pea casserole supreme
directions: Melt margarine and add green pepper, onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix and freeze in 8x12 pan. Remove from freezer about an hour before serving.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding applies and nuts last.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut as a pie. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes one 9-inch cake.

title: oven roasted fries(alternative to french fries in oil)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut potatoes in half, then in even slices.
In a bowl, mix oil and seasonings.
Add potatoes a little at a time and coat with oil mixture.
Drain potatoes of extra oil and place on a cookie sheet in a single layer and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hamburger dish
directions: Brown ground beef.
Into a greased casserole dish, layer ground beef, thinly sliced potatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Use as many layers as you want, but end with potatoes and onion.
Pour soup over top. Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken paprika(crock-pot meal)
directions: Saute onions in oil and paprika until tender and bright red. Add broth.
Largely chunk chicken and add.
Place in crock and cook until very tender (about 4 plus hours).
Mix sour cream and flour together.
Add to chicken 5 minutes before serving.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.
Great with French bread.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in bananas
and
lemon
juice.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add
to
cream
mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: miniature quiche
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and flour.
Press into miniature muffin pans.
Mix eggs, half and half, Swiss cheese, bacon, chives, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into shells.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 20 minutes.
Makes 36.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in a large bowl or rectangular dish.
Top each 7th layer with sour cream and mayonnaise (for the amount, use 3/4 pint of sour cream and an equal amount of mayonnaise).

title: crock-pot dip
directions: Brown meat; drain well.
Combine next 6 ingredients and place in crock-pot.
Set on high.
When all cheeses are melted, add remaining ingredients until well blended.
Turn crock-pot on low until ready to serve.
May also be used as a topping for nacho chips or baked potatoes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in buttermilk; set aside.

title: chicken wrap-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, onions, garlic and curry together.
Roll mixture into 6 balls.
Place balls in center of chicken breast and fold around ball.
Wrap two strips of bacon crisscrossing them to hold filling in.
Secure with toothpick.
Place in baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and whipped topping until creamy.
Pour into graham cracker crust evenly.
Refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.

title: oven stew
directions: Place meat and vegetables in a roaster. Sprinkle with salt, sugar, pepper and tapioca.
Pour tomato juice over.
Cover and bake in a preheated 300° oven for 4 hours. Stir occasionally.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: dessert plums
directions: Cut the
plums in half and remove the seeds.
Place the prepared plums
in	a
quart
glass bowl and add sugar to your taste.
Microwave
on
High for 10 to 15 minutes, depending on the amount
of plums you are preparing.
Stir about every five minutes.

title: chili mac
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on box.
Drain.
Brown hamburger and onions in a large skillet.
Add tomatoes, water and spaghetti. Bring to an almost boil, stirring constantly; salt and pepper to taste.
Add chili powder and simmer 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain grease.
Add Sloppy Joes mix, chili beans, tomato sauce and onions.
Add water and heat.
Pour into baking pan.
Top with chips and cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cheese cake(very simple)
directions: Beat cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add 1 cup of sugar gradually and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Prepare graham cracker crust in bottom of spring-form pan.
Add mixed ingredients.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking, combine topping mixture of sour cream, 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; mix well.
Remove cake from oven and spread topping over all.
Bake 20 minutes more.
Let cool and unspring. Makes 12 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: microwavable individual meat loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients except for barbecue sauce.
Divide mixture into 6 parts, shape into loaves.
Arrange on rack in rectangular baking dish (12 x 7 x 2 x 2-inches).
Spread each loaf with about 1 teaspoon barbecue sauce.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High (100%) 5 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Microwave until meat loaves are almost done, 7 to 9 minutes longer.
Let stand, covered, 3 minutes.
Spread with additional barbecue sauce, if desired.

title: refrigerator strawberry pie
directions: Clean strawberries and cut into small pieces.
Mix sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes. Dissolve over low heat and combine with berry mixture.
Fold in whip cream.
Add vanilla and turn into crust.
Chill for 1 1/2 hours until firm.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add hot water, a little at a time, until mixture becomes stiff dough.
Flour hands and knead well.
Divide dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness, being sure not to get them too thin.
Shape (with a knife) dough into triangle pieces.
Deep fry pieces in very hot cooking oil.
Remove when browned; roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Serve with a side of honey, if desired.
These are wonderful!
A great dessert with a Mexican meal.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil the chicken in salted water until tender. Remove chicken from broth.
Cool and remove skin and bones from chicken.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Use chicken broth to cook the spaghetti. Drain.
Using a small amount of cooking oil, simmer the peppers, celery and onions.
In a very large bowl, mix the chopped chicken, vegetables, spaghetti, soup, black pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into casserole dishes and top generously with the cheese.
Cover and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Tastier if made the day before and refrigerated.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
While cake is baking, cap and slice strawberries and sugar.
When cake is done and is still hot, use the handle of a wooden spoon and poke holes all over cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk on cake evenly.
Pour strawberries over cake and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until chilled before serving.
Cake is better the longer it sets.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 15-inch pan, layer ingredients, starting with pie filling.
Cut up butter and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 package of crescent rolls in greased pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla until creamy.
Spread on top of rolls and top with the other package of rolls.
Top with unbeaten egg white and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet supper(easy one dish meal!)
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in a little oil.
Add rest of ingredients except sour cream.
Cover and simmer until macaroni is tender.
Add sour cream, if desired, at end, but do not let boil again or it might separate.

title: ribbon jello
directions: Make all 3 boxes of Jell-O.
Keep in 3 separate bowls.
Add cream cheese to 1 bowl of Jell-O.
Mix until well blended.
Then take a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, add 1 bowl of Jell-O and let set in fridge until set.
Then add the bowl of Jell-O with cream cheese in it.
Let it become set up in fridge, then add last bowl of Jell-O. Let set, then cover top with whipped cream.

title: zesty italian pot roast
directions: Place potatoes, carrots and celery in 3 1/2-quart slow cooker. Season roast with pepper and place on top. Mix soup and water. Pour over top of meat. Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours. Turn on high and cook 5 to 6 hours.

title: potato latkes
directions: In bowl of food processor, insert shredding blade and cover. Shred potatoes with skins and onion.
You can also do this with a hand grater.

title: sausage roll
directions: Mix Bisquick, oleo and milk together.
Mix the sausages (uncooked) and chilies together.
Divide dough in half.
Roll into rectangle, spread sausage on dough.
Roll up like jelly roll. Slice in 1-inch pieces.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg and vanilla; mix one minute.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix for one minute. Mix half of dough with red food coloring.
Chill well before using.
Roll one of each color into a snake roll with floured hands.
Twist the 2 colors together and shape into a candy cane. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts and press in large oblong dish. Bake for 3 minutes at 350 degrees. Let cool completely.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies(preacher cookies)
directions: Add first four ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Cool and eat.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Measure dry ingredients, then sift together.
Add bananas along with oil, vanilla, eggs and pineapple with juice.
Blend and pour into a 9-inch greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or icing, if desired.

title: easy cookies
directions: Cook together first three ingredients 5 minutes (plus or minus) until thickened.
Break graham crackers in half and place side by side on greased cookie sheet.
Pour cooked mixture over crackers and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven. Remove at once to piece of waxed paper to cool.

title: apple gingerbread with cream cheese and nuts
directions: Stir together apple slices, 2 tablespoons of the butter and brown sugar in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes until apples soften.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and salt onto wax paper.
Sift again.
Beat together oil and granulated sugar in large bowl; mix 1 minute.
Add egg and 1/2 teaspoon of the vanilla and beat 2 minutes or more until light and thick.
Combine boiling water, molasses in small saucepan.
Stir well.
Add to oil, sugar mixture alternately with dry sifted ingredients.
Pour into pan over apples.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: bubble cake
directions: Thaw bread and snip 1 loaf in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt oleo. Add brown sugar, cinnamon and milk. Pour this over bread. Sprinkle pudding on top of this.
Snip another loaf of bread after that (let raise).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Flip over on cookie sheet when done.

title: fruit trifle
directions: Combine and mix pudding mix, 3 cups milk, 1/2 cup pineapple juice and 8 ounces sour cream.
Add fruit. Layer cake and vanilla fruit pudding, 3 layers cake and 3 layers fruit mixture.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: meal in a casserole
directions: Mix meat, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Press in a deep baking dish.
Place Irish potatoes
on
top of meat, then the sliced onions and bell pepper.
Mix;
pour	over all. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix Jell-O into Cool Whip and then add cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Add pineapple and coconut; mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: cucumber rounds
directions: Mix together.
Spread on round pumpernickel bread.
Top with piece of cucumber.

title: easy fresh peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Spread half of mixture into bottom of pie shell.
Arrange sliced peaches over mixture.
Add other 1/2 mixture over top of peaches.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° about 1 hour or until juices thicken and crust is light brown.

title: low-fat breakfast casserole
directions: Spray no-fat oil on 10 x 10-inch or larger pie plate.
Layer the sausage, salsa, onion, cheese and eggs.
Mix Bisquick and milk powder.
Add water; mix and pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes, until top is brown.
Bake at 350° if using a Pyrex dish.
May be frozen and reheated in microwave.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry yogurt coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and lightly flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In large bowl, blend cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, yogurt and oil.
Beat with electric mixer on high 3 minutes. Scrape bowl often.
Spread 2/3 of batter in pan.
Spoon cranberry sauce evenly over batter.
Spoon remaining batter evenly over cranberry sauce.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 35 minutes on rack.
Makes 20 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew chicken in water until tender.
Remove chicken and set aside to cool.
Debone and cut into small pieces.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute celery, onion and bell pepper with butter until tender. Add soups and sauteed mixture to spaghetti.
Add chicken and 1/2 cheese.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish (greased).
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until cheese melts or microwave until cheese melts.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mash raw ground chuck in casserole dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with chopped onion, cream of mushroom soup and Tater Tots.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour until meat is done and Tater Tots are brown.

title: peach punch
directions: Put peaches in blender until pureed.
Mix with peach drink. Serve cold.

title: wonder salad
directions: Drain and discard canned liquids.
Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator if tightly covered.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over moderate heat until thick, stirring
constantly.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell and cover with
meringue made of egg whites and 6 tablespoons of sugar. Bake in moderate oven until brown.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt. Bring to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add soda and butter flavoring.
Pour over popped corn. Toss gently.
Spread on cookie sheets. Place in a 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Store in tight container.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl except the salmon.
Then add salmon and fold into mixture so as not to break up the salmon. Make into patties and fry.

title: creole peas
directions: Chop vegetables; saute in bacon drippings until tender.
Add peas, tomato soup, bacon pieces and seasoning.
Layer peas, mushroom soup and egg slices.
Makes 2 layers.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Mushroom soup melts when heated.
Heat at 300° to 325° until bubbly.
Yields 20 servings.

title: hash brown omelet
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Leave drippings in skillet; remove bacon and crumble.
Mix potatoes, onion and green pepper; pat into skillet.
Cook over low heat until underside is crisp and brown.
Blend eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over potatoes.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Cover; cook over low heat.
When egg is done, loosen omelet.
Fold in half.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot dish
directions: Mix together.
Put in casserole dish and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli in food processor.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in pie pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
This is good topped with Cool Whip or whip cream.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water to cover 30 minutes or until tender.
Let cool to touch; peel and mash potatoes.
Combine potatoes and next 6 ingredients and spoon evenly into 2 lightly greased 9-inch pie plates.
Combine brown sugar, pecans and flour; sprinkle evenly over potato mixture.
Drizzle evenly with 1/3 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Put stew beef, onions and 1 1/2 c. broth in a large pot. Bring to a boil, simmer for about 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Add remaining broth, carrots, celery and potatoes. Cook for 30 minutes longer. (I also add one pack beef stew seasoning mix to this before cooking.)

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix salmon, egg and flour.
Take 1/4 cup of liquid and add baking powder.
Mix until foamy.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons into hot oil and fry until golden.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger; add tomato paste, water and spaghetti sauce mix.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan:
noodles, meat mixture, cottage cheese, noodles, meat mixture and Mozzarella.
Repeat; Mozzarella on very top.
Serves 8 persons; 1/2 to 4 persons.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon pull-aparts
directions: Lightly grease or spray tube pan.
Place frozen dough balls in tube pan.
Sprinkle pudding over dough balls.
Pour melted butter, brown sugar and cinnamon over pudding and dough.
Top with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Cover and set overnight at room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sister floy guffey's pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening, then add 4 eggs.
Beat two minutes. Add two more eggs and plain flour.
Add just a pinch of salt and flavoring.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked orange roughy
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or broil until fish flakes.

title: taco salad casserole
directions: Layer in a rectangular pan: lettuce and tomatoes. Mix together sour cream, Miracle Whip and lemon juice. Spread over lettuce.
Brown hamburger; add taco seasoning, salt and pepper. Spread over sour cream mixture. Crush up taco chips and spread over hamburger mixture. Sprinkle cheese over chips and broil until melted.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill overnight.
Drop by teaspoonful into powdered sugar.
Shape into balls.
Bake in greased cookie sheet at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour pineapple into pan.
Toss together apples, 1/4 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Place on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle fruit layers with dry cake mix.
Top with melted margarine and 1/4 cup sugar.
Top this with chopped pecans.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cut with knife to allow juice to rise to top.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: sombreros
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: fresh corn and pepper bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch round baking pan.
In large bowl, combine flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In small bowl, combine buttermilk, butter and egg.

title: praline bars
directions: Cook butter and sugar 10 minutes.
Let boil for 2 minutes. Stir and scrape down side of pan.
Remove from heat and add nuts. Spoon over crackers.
Spread on greased pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: covered up chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Tear into bite size pieced. Place in casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and undiluted soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Place stuffing mix on top.
Cover. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine broccoli and onion.
Cook all according to package. Drain and add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour into a greased 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Put some shredded cheese on and melt.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
One small jar of chopped pimento adds color; it's up to you.

title: pizza bake
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add onions and peppers.
Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain macaroni and add to sausage.
Mix in pizza sauce.
Put in baking dish.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hash brown potatoes casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together cheese, sour cream, onion, soup and salt and pour over potatoes. Top with crushed cornflakes and pour melted butter over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass pan, cover bottom 1 1/4-inches deep with lettuce.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and sugar; layer bacon, eggs, frozen peas and rest of lettuce.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and sugar. Layer onions, mayo and cheese.
Sprinkle top with paprika.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut slice from top of baked potato or half a large one lengthwise.
Scoop out inside; mash and add hot milk, butter and seasonings.
Beat until fluffy.
Pile lightly into shells and return to oven to brown slightly, if desired.
Add finely chopped onion, stiffly beaten egg white or cheese before returning to oven.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cut chicken from bone and into strips.
Brown chicken; dice onion and bell pepper in garlic and oil.

title: pepper salad
directions: Combine all salad ingredients in bowl.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning.
Mix oil and vinegar together.
Pour over salad. Let marinate several hours or overnight before serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream together butter, powdered sugar and vanilla until light. Add flour and nuts. Mix well. Shape into small balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Alternate layer of potatoes, green peppers and onions in greased baking dish.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Mix mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: magic marshmallow puffs(easy and good!)
directions: Dip marshmallows in melted butter, then roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place 1 sugar coated marshmallow in center of 1 section of crescent roll.
Wrap crescent roll tightly around marshmallows to seal.
Dip entire roll in melted butter, then place in muffin tin.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tail gate chili
directions: Brown meat in stew pot; drain good.
Add onions, peppers and garlic; cook until tender.
Add tomatoes and spices.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Add beans.
Simmer 30 minutes longer.

title: candy apple delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: spicy chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, onion and pepper together.
Heat; bring to boil.
Stir often.
Layer tortilla shell, chicken mix and cheese (layer 2 times).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Can be warmed over.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat sugar and eggs with remaining ingredients.
Fill with milk to line on freezer and freeze.
(I use 2% milk).

title: scalloped seafood
directions: Use tuna, crab, lobster or shrimp and scallops.
Butter casserole; cover
bottom
with
rolled
cracker crumbs.
Add a layer of seafood,
more
crumbs,
then more seafood.
Top with potato chips, crushed.
Pour
2 cups rich milk over all.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350° until done.

title: taco salad
directions: Place ingredients in order on pizza pan.
Place Tostitos around edge.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix everything together and let raise until double in bulk. Makes enough pizza dough for 2 cookie sheets.

title: my grandma stroud's chocolate pie
directions: Fill 2 unbaked pie shells.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together, except for cheese. Put into a greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch); top with cheese. Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: irish stew
directions: Trim fat from the mutton and cut meat into pieces.
Put into a saucepot and add just enough water to cover meat.
Cook, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Meanwhile, cut onions into quarters, cut carrots and cabbage into strips and quarter the potatoes.

title: husband's delight
directions: Add sugar, garlic, tomato sauce, salt and pepper to ground beef.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook and drain noodles. Chop green onions, blend well with cream cheese and sour cream. Grease baking dish lightly.
Layer noodles, meat sauce sour cream mix and 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Repeat, ending with Cheddar on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: sausage brunch eggs
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch dish. Sprinkle with croutons.
Beat eggs with 2 1/2 cups milk and pour over all.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and refrigerate overnight. Before baking, blend soup with 1/2 cup milk and pour over all. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Let sit before cutting.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa.
Add eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix until well blended.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle small marshmallows to cover cake.
Prepare icing last 5 minutes of baking.

title: morning call doughnuts
directions: Mix milk, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and salt in pan.
Heat until shortening is melted.
Cool until lukewarm.
Put warm water into large bowl.
Add yeast.
Add lukewarm milk and egg.
Beat in 2 cups flour and nutmeg.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn on floured board.
Knead 5 minutes.
Put dough in greased bowl.
Turn dough over to bring greased side up.
Cover with damp towel.
Let rise in warm place, 85° free from draft, about 1 or 1 1/2 hours or until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Knead.
Let rest a minute to make rolling easier.
Roll 1/4-inch thick into rectangle.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch squares.
Cover with towel.
Let rise 30 minutes or until almost double.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, sugar, salt, eggs and soda. Add flour, vanilla, chopped nuts and potato chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet sandwiches
directions: Grind raisins and marshmallows together.
Spread a little orange juice to make mixture spreadable.
Serve on Town House crackers.

title: pickles
directions: Dissolve 2 cups sugar in one cup of vinegar.
Pour over mixture of first 5 ingredients.
Stir and refrigerate.
Will keep for 6 months.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Butter a 3-quart casserole dish.
Layer first 7 ingredients. Mix remaining ingredients except paprika.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake 3 hours at 325°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: *Or use cinnamon and nutmeg for spice cookies and raisins. For chocolate chip cookies, add 2 packages (12 ounces) each and 2 cups chopped nuts.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In glass dish, layer each row, do not stir.
Refrigerate overnight.
You can use whatever you want like broccoli, cauliflower, bell pepper, mushrooms or tomatoes.
We garnish with sliced eggs.

title: easy jello
directions: Sprinkle jello over cottage cheese.
Add drained oranges and pineapple; mix gently.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix.
Refrigerate. Refreshing as an appetizer, side dish or dessert.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pour rice in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine soup and water; spoon over rice.
Top with onion.
Season chicken with salt and pepper and brown in skillet.
Place chicken over rice, add drippings from skillet.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 375°.
(This recipe can be adapted for microwave oven by using a glass dish and reducing cooking time to 30 to 45 minutes.)
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Place apples and undiluted apple juice into a large pan. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for about 5 minutes. Dissolve cornstarch in water. Gently stir cornstarch into apple mixture. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes or until apples begin to soften. Stir in cinnamon and nutmeg. Fill pastry shell with apples; dot with butter and cover with top crust. Sprinkle crust with Sugar Twin. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
In a bowl, combine the flour, salt and freshly ground pepper.
Dredge chicken pieces in mixture.
Shake off excess flour.
In a skillet, heat butter. Brown chicken on all sides until golden brown.
Transfer to a Dutch oven.
Peel and chop onion.
Saute in skillet for about 3 minutes until transparent.
Add to chicken.
Add cider and water. Season with tarragon and garlic.
Cook, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut apples into wedges.
Remove cores.
Add to chicken. Cook for another 10 minutes.
Add creme fraiche or sour cream. Cook for 10 minutes.
Add calvados.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve steaming hot, sprinkled with parsley.

title: chili dip
directions: Cut up cheese; mix with chili and chilies.
Microwave until cheese is completely melted.
Or bake at 350° about 20 minutes until cheese melts.
Use plain Doritos and dip.

title: n m cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 2 eggs and spread in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch sheet cake pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs; pour over cake mixture.
Spread chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: greek chicken with green olives
directions: In a large skillet with cover, brown small pieces of chicken on high flame for about 10 minutes.
Add sliced onions, olives, stewed tomatoes, oregano, garlic and white wine.
Bring to a boil, about 2 minutes.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Serve over your favorite rice.

title: spoon bread
directions: Pour boiling water over meal, beating constantly to prevent lumping.
Let cool.
Add butter, sugar, and salt.
Add eggs, baking powder, and milk.
Bake at 425° in casserole dish for 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and water.
Add flour. Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Shape into small balls or fingers. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven, 325°, for 20 minutes. Remove to rack; cool slightly and roll in confectioners (xxxx) sugar.

title: lime pickles
directions: Slice the cucumbers and soak in mixture of lime
and water for 24 hours. Rinse 3 times with cold water.
Cover with cold water and soak 3 hours, then drain.
Mix the vinegar, salt, celery seed, cloves and pickling spices.
Pour over cucumbers. Soak overnight. Add a little green food coloring. Drain in big pan. Bring to a boil for 25 minutes.
Pack jars with cucumbers.

title: pot roast in sour cream
directions: Brown roast on all sides in hot oil in a large Dutch oven. Combine 1/2 cup of water and bouillon.
Add to Dutch oven.
Add bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Add onions and carrots; cover and cook 30 minutes or until vegetables and meat are tender.
Remove roast and vegetables from Dutch oven; keep warm.
Remove bay leaf; discard.
Combine flour and 3 tablespoons of water.
Stir into pan drippings.
Cook, stirring constantly until gravy is smooth and thickened.
Add sour cream and vegetables to gravy, stirring constantly until thoroughly heated.
Place cooked noodles on a serving platter. Slice roast and arrange over noodles.
Serve with gravy.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave broccoli-cheese-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in casserole dish on High for 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Stir; then microwave on High for another 5 minutes.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Can use any cream type soup.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Scald the milk.
Mix together the eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir milk gradually into egg mixture.
Pour into prepared 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 30 minutes, or until a knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool before serving.

title: skillet chicken pot pie
directions: Heat soup, 1 cup milk, vegetables, chicken, and pepper in medium skillet over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have crust ready.
Combine ingredients and mix in blender until smooth.
Pour into chilled pie shell and bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients very well, then chill before serving.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with sugar and margarine.
Save 1/4 cup for top.
Spread in sheet pan (11 x 13-inch) or a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Dream Whip and spread on crust. Next, layer cherry pie filling, then the remainder of Dream Whip. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup crumbs.
Chill to serve.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown meats and onion together and drain off excess fat; combine with catsup, mustard, vinegar, brown sugar and salt.
Add pork and beans, green lima beans and red kidney beans.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: congressional chicken
directions: Combine soups and milk.
Mix 1 1/2 cups of soup mixture with rice; pour into buttered casserole dish.
Place chicken on top and cover with remaining soup. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with cheese and continue baking for 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy baked beans
directions: In pan, put the beans and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Heat to simmer.
Serve with fresh 1-inch thick slices of Italian bread with or without buttering.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cut artichokes into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: esau's pottage(thick lentil and bean soup)
directions: Cover peas, lentils, barley and beans to twice their depth in cold water.
Soak overnight.
Drain and rinse thoroughly.
Simmer beef bones and salt in 2 quarts water about 15 minutes.
Skim. Add peas, lentils, barley, beans, carrots, celery, onion, parsley, pepper, and bouillon cubes.
Simmer, covered 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove meat from bones; return meat to soup.
Serves 6.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Thaw shrimp.
Rinse with cold water.
Place in boiling water and simmer about 10 minutes.
Drain and arrange onions and shrimp in alternate layers.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and chill about 6 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain and serve on green salad.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in salt water until tender.
Place in baking dish.
Chop broccoli and mix with remaining ingredients. Pour over chicken.	Cover with bread crumbs and pats of butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well in large bowl.
Form into bite size balls and place on cookie sheet.
(May use mini muffin pans-adjust oven time and temp.)
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
May be frozen and rewarmed.
Makes 100 balls.

title: okra succotash
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pot; cook until okra and onions are done.
Serve over white or brown rice.

title: bulgogi beef(korean barbecue)
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate beef just before cooking. Serve with sticky rice.
For more flavor, add gochujan (2 tablespoons of soybean paste, cayenne pepper and soy sauce).

title: stuffed cabbage for sukkot
directions: Core the cabbage and discard the top few bitter leaves. Boil enough water to cover the cabbage. Put the cabbage carefully into the hot water, and cook covered for approximately 12 minutes (longer if you want very soft leaves). Remove the head, plunge it into cold water and drain.

title: party punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; add teas, lemon, orange and pineapple juices.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Add cherries with juice, ice water and ginger ale.
Pour into tall glasses, 3/4 full of cracked ice.
Yields 75 servings.

title: emily's ginger creams
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and molasses; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Shape into small balls (1-inch).
Dip 1/2 surface into granulated sugar.
Bake 2 1/2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, saving juice.
Crush salmon and stir in eggs, salmon juice and cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Add salt, pepper and lemon juice, mixing well.
Shape into patties and fry in hot shortening until golden brown.
This makes 5 servings.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes. Strain and enjoy.

title: bakery lane soup bowl's portuguese vegetable soup
directions: Slice kielbasa thinly.
Place in a skillet and cover with water.
Bring to boil and cook until all water evaporates.
Remove to paper towel with slotted spoon.

title: cheryl's lemon chiffon pie
directions: Mix gelatin with only 1/2 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup ice cubes. Mix pudding with only 1 cup of milk. Blend jello and pudding.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour in pie crust and chill at least 4 hours before serving.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients. Chill. Serve and enjoy.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Puree cranberries and orange in a food processor.
Stir in sugar and let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Prepare Jell-O with boiling water and cool.
When Jell-O begins to set, combine all ingredients and pour into mold.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and cool pasta.
Stir in all ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Chill.
Before serving, stir in the Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken swiss casserole
directions: Place slices of Swiss cheese in an 8 x 10-inch baking pan. Add boneless chicken, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Combine cream of chicken soup and milk over chicken.
Cover with a layer of stuffing.
Pour melted butter over stuffing and cook at 350° for one hour.

title: lime delight salad
directions: Stir jello in boiling water until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and marshmallows to hot liquid.
Stir to dissolve.
Cool until syrupy.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Stir together ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with shrimp.

title: apple crumb kuchen
directions: Combine pecans, brown sugar, flour, sugar, cinnamon and margarine together until crumbly.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in double boiler. Beat 1 minute.
When water boils, remove and continue beating several minutes.

title: good apple pie
directions: Mix flour, salt and 3/4 cup butter well, then add water. Divide dough in half.
Roll half and put in a 10-inch pie plate. Spread 1/3 of sugar on crust, then half the apples, 1/3 more sugar, then remainder of apples, then remainder of sugar.
Slice 3/4 stick of butter; lay on top.
Sprinkle with spices.
Roll remaining half of dough, making top crust.
Spread over apple mixture, fluting edges.
Cut slits in top crust.
Brush top crust with milk and sprinkle a little sugar on top.
Place on a cookie sheet and cook on bottom rack of 400° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls(makes 24 rolls)
directions: One tablespoon RapidRise yeast equals 1 package active dry yeast (cuts rising time in half).

title: stuffed flank steak
directions: Combine stuffing mix, water and butter.
Let stand 5 minutes. Spoon stuffing on steak, leaving 1-inch border.
Add scallions and pepper, then roll from long edge.
Secure with wooden picks. Place seam side down in baking pan or microwave safe dish.
tags: Stove Top flexible serving stuffing mix

title: jiffy tomato aspic
directions: Bring tomato juice to boiling point.
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in celery, green pepper, onion, salt and vinegar. Pour into mold or appropriate size Pyrex dish and refrigerate. Unmold or cut into squares onto lettuce lined plate(s).
Serve with mayonnaise, if desired.

title: grape spritzer
directions: Place 1 lime slice in each of 8 glasses.
Combine Club soda and grape juice.
Pour 1 cup mixture over lime slice in each glass. Has 50 calories and 40 mg. sodium.

title: caramel pie
directions: Cook all but last two ingredients together until it thickens. While cooking, brown 1/3 cup sugar and add boiling water to the browned sugar.
Cook until smooth.
Add to mixture. Pour into crust and bake until done.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce and orange rind.
Chill until slightly thickened, using wire whip. Blend in 3 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish with rest of Cool Whip, cranberries and orange slices, if desired.
Makes 5 1/3 cups or 10 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, oleo and cream cheese in a bowl. Alternately add flour and eggs, beginning and ending with flour. With mixer, beat 30 to 60 seconds, until well blended.
Pour mixture into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Start from a cold oven and bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: beef bologna
directions: Mix the seasoning together, then add to ground beef and mix thoroughly.
Let set at least 12 hours before canning.
If left in cold place, you can
let set for several days.
Put in cans and cook 3 hours in hot
water
bath or 1 1/2 hours at 10 pound pressure in pressure
cooker.
I
add
a little water in each jar before sealing.

title: hot hush puppies
directions: Fill a large deep-fry pot or electric skillet to half its depth with wesson oil. Heat oil to 400°, meanwhile, in a large bowl sift together cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and garlic salt, blend well. Add onion and jalapeno pepper, stir until well blended. In a small bowl combine buttermilk and eggs, add to dry ingredients, stir until batter is moist and all ingredients are combined. Working in small batches carefully drop butter by heaping tablespoons into hot oil. Fry until golden brown.
Makes about 36.

title: fried ground hog
directions: Skin and clean	ground	hog
the
same	way you would a rabbit or squirrel.
Wash	and
soak
in
cold water for a few hours. Boil in salted water until tender.	Dip in well beaten egg and milk mixture, then roll
in
flour until well covered. Fry in deep fat until tender.
Start
with
hot frying oil and cut heat down and simmer until tender.

title: baked potatoes elegante
directions: Cut slice on top of each potato and scoop out inside.
Mash. Add all ingredients (except cheese and bacon); beat until smooth. Fill shells and return to oven until heated.
Top with cheese and bacon!

title: cocoa chocolate filling
directions: Cook 10 or 15 minutes. Add butter and vanilla. Beat until desired spreading consistency.

title: crispy eggplant sandwiches
directions: Slice eggplant into 1/2-inch slices.
You should have about 8 to 10 slices.
Place a slice of cheese on half the eggplant slices.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Top with remaining slices.
Dip sandwiches in egg.
Combine the bread crumbs, cheese and parsley. Dip sandwiches in crumb mixture.
Place on baking sheets.
Drizzle each sandwich with 1 teaspoon oil.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with a slice of tomato between 2 slices of bread.

title: beef barbecue sandwiches
directions: 2 tablespoons granulated sugar = 1/2 teaspoon Sweet 'N Low.

title: frankfurter casserole (on chips)
directions: Brown franks in oil.
Remove.
Saute onions and peppers in remaining oil until tender.
Add tomatoes and spices.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Add franks; simmer 5 minutes longer. Serve hot on potato chips.
Serves 6.

title: 6 weeks bran muffins
directions: *Cinnamon, allspice, ginger and nutmeg.

title: party potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter, then add thawed potatoes, celery soup, sour cream, both cheeses, salt and pepper and garlic.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish at 325° for 1 hour or until bubbly and golden.

title: pfeffernusse
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar, egg, molasses and anise or almond flavoring.
Measure flour.
Blend dry ingredients and mix in gradually with hands.
Knead dough until right consistency for molding.
If dough seems too soft, refrigerate until firm.
Mold into "snakes" 3/4-inch in diameter and cut into 14-inch bits with floured knife and arrange on a greased baking sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Cookies will harden on standing and should have a nutlike crunch.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chicken divan(great cook ahead dish)
directions: Cook broccoli, drain, and place into buttered dish.
Break up 3 whole cooked chicken breasts and put on top of broccoli. Combine remaining ingredients cooking until cheese melts.
Pour cooked sauce over chicken and broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 - 40 minutes.
Brown at the end of cooking time.

title: salsa sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add tomatillos, cilantro, water, salt and peppers to your taste.
(If you prefer a milder pepper, use it.)
Simmer until thick (approximately 30 minutes). Store in refrigerator or freezer.
To process in jars, follow directions in your pressure cooker or canning booklets.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine butter, eggs, whole and cream corn, sour cream and muffin mix in bowl. Mix well. Spoon into a 1 1/2 qt. baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: make your own ranch dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender or food processor.
Puree until smooth.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt oleo and sugar; beat eggs and mix all ingredients.
Bake in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.

title: shell-mera(ecuador-banana muffins)
directions: Beat well shortening and egg.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in oatmeal, nuts, raisins and also bananas. Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with other ingredients.
Mixture will be fairly soft.
Chill slightly, then form into a ball.
Roll in minced pecans.
Chill until time to serve.
Serves 20 to 30.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan.
Thoroughly combine thawed strawberries and syrup with dry gelatin.
Set aside.

title: raisin mumbles
directions: Cook until thickened and cool slightly.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Crush crackers and mix with melted oleo, mix in nuts and set aside 1 cup of mixture to go on top.
Add milk and pudding mix with ice cream and whip with mixer until well mixed.
Pour in crust and spread Cool Whip over ice cream mixture after you get it in pan.
Sprinkle with remainder of mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: breakfast dish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: parsley soup and hot dogs
directions: Put the noodles in a pot on the stove for 6 minutes.
Mix it. When it's done, you put parsley in with the chicken and a little egg.
Mix it for 1 more.
Then it's done.
Freeze them (hot dogs) in the freezer.
Then put them in a pot on the stove.
I don't know what minute; maybe it's 5.
Pick up the hot dogs with a fork and put it on the bun and then on a plate.
Put ketchup and mustard on it.

title: plum relish
directions: Wash plums; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Drain. Cover with water.
Boil until tender; drain and mash fine.
Add sugar and other ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and slice potatoes into 1/8 to 1/4 inch slices. Layer potatoes and cheese in a baking dish and top with soup. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or more until top begins to brown lightly.
Let cool for 5 minutes before serving.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and apples. Mix on high speed.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased Bundt tube pan. Add 1 1/2 apples, 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and 1/2 of remaining sugar.
Repeat layer.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: beet salad with horseradish
directions: In dish, place cooked beets and onion, sliced thin.
Use another bowl and add together all other ingredients.
Pour juice mixture over beets and onions; refrigerate at least 3 hours (will keep 3 to 4 days).
Serve with deviled eggs or smoked fish.

title: karo cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and half of Karo gradually. Cream until fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time and beat well. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and beaten egg whites.
Add remaining Karo gradually, beating until stiff meringue is formed.
Add to batter.
Makes 2 layers.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven until done.

title: apple streusel
directions: Into bottom of a buttered dish put thick layer of apples. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixed.
Dot with lumps of butter. Into a bowl sift the next four ingredients.
Break egg into bowl and mix until crumbly.
Put over top of apples.
Bake at 350° until top is brown, about 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Bake in vegetable sprayed loaf pan 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for approximately 1/2 hour.
Cool on rack until serving temperature.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Make out in small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Mash out with fork.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: green chilie quiche
directions: Sprinkle one of the cheeses on bottom of pie shell. Add green chilies on top. Pour mixture of eggs, milk, cumin, salt and pepper over chilies. Put other cheese on top. (May add already browned sausage to mixture, if desired.) Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°. Needs to cool 15 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Dip each chicken breast in sour cream or dip, then roll in chips.
Place in ovenproof, flat, glass baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Heat oleo until melted.
Drizzle oleo over chicken in dish. Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes. Do not overbake; it will become dry and not a good leftover dish.
Easy. Can be made in advance and stored in refrigerator in covered dish until ready to bake.

title: tortilla stack
directions: Mix all ingredients together and layer onto tortillas.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix well. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture.
Add alternately with water.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until test shows done.

title: sticky rolls
directions: The night before, butter Bundt pan well.
Put the rolls into pan.
Sprinkle the dry pudding over the rolls.
Sprinkle cinnamon over the pudding and pecans.
In a saucepan, melt the butter.
Add the brown sugar and bring to a boil.
Cool for a few minutes and stir in the vanilla.
Pour over frozen rolls and let sit until morning.

title: strawberry pie in meringue crust
directions: Beat egg whites until forms soft peaks; gradually add sugar and vanilla and beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in cracker crumbs and pecans.
Spread mixture in buttered 10-inch pie pan, spreading sides slightly higher.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or brown.
Cool.

title: breakfast strata
directions: Cut the bread into cubes, place in an 8 in. baking pan.
Add ham, sausage, onion, cheese and butter.
Mix the eggs with milk and mustard.
Pour egg mixture over other ingredients.
Prepare the night before.
Bake at 350° until well set.

title: russian tea
directions: More spices can be added, if desired.
One teaspoon makes a cup of tea.
This can be mixed and stored in a dry jar.

title: grape jelly
directions: Boil for 20 minutes and put through Foley Mill.
Fill jars and seal.
May be frozen as well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, cheese, soup, salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, water, garlic salt, salt and pepper. Shape into small balls.
Combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice in a large skillet, stirring, until jelly has melted.
Add meat balls and simmer uncovered at least 45 minutes.
Serve in chafing dish.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add sugar and flour.
Put into pizza pan and press evenly with fingers.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool completely.

title: tamala pie
directions: Saut onions and garlic in bacon drippings; add meat and brown. Add the seasonings and simmer. Cook grits and then stir into meat mixture. Grease baking dish, then pour into baking dish. Top with shredded cheese. Bake in 350° preheated oven until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Allow cooling about 10 minutes before serving.

title: orange jello sherbet dessert
directions: Add orange sherbet to jello;
mix well.
When partially set, add oranges and fold in whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Mix together oatmeal, sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Spread on a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
It will look gooey.
Let set for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in dish (9 x 13-inch).
Heat soup and cheese together.
Just before all cheese is melted, add milk, mayonnaise and egg. Stir until smooth and creamy.
Pour on top of broccoli. Stir butter and bread crumbs together.
Put on top of dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts and chop up finely (a food processor works great). To the chicken, add the lemon juice and pecans. Mix well. Add salt and the amount of mayonnaise to suit the desired consistency.

title: golden pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in butter.
Pour in stewed tomatoes, mushroom soup and 3/4 to 1 can of water.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Cook sugar, dates and milk until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add nuts and beat until thick.
Then pour on a wet cloth and roll.
When cool, remove cloth and slice.

title: chile con queso
directions: Melt both cheeses together on low heat of electric surface unit.
After cheese melts, add cream, stirring constantly.
Add chopped tomato, chopped green chiles and garlic powder.
Stir to blend all flavors.
Add more cream if desired.
Serve warm in skillet or chafing dish with Tostados.

title: deli roasted chicken pate
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Remove skin and bones; discard.
Cut chicken into small pieces, making about 3 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and sour cream with chicken.
Make crust on bottom and top out of crushed crackers and melted butter.
Sprinkle with poppy seed (optional).
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: greek spinach casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees. Heat spinach and squeeze all the water out. Place one can of crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish, press seams together to make crust. Brush top with 1-2 Tbsp. olive oil. Bake 5 minutes (do not over bake). Allow to cool slightly.

title: company chicken
directions: Place chicken in oblong casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup together and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: crabbies
directions: Blend all ingredients (except muffins) together and spread on English muffins.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cut in quarters and serve hot.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix together and spread on crust.
Top with blueberry pie filling or one of your choice.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Pour over 6 to 10 pound roast in covered roaster.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 hours.
Stir every hour.
Meat will fall apart in 5 or 6 hours.

title: brunch egg bake
directions: In a large bowl, toss cheese and sprinkle half in an ungreased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Saute mushrooms, onion, and pepper with butter until tender.
Layer over cheese.
Spread ham or sausage over vegetables and sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.
Blend flour, milk and eggs and pour mixture over layers. Bake in a 350 degree oven for 35-45 minutes.

title: new potatoes and parsley
directions: Brush and scrub the potatoes well, leaving skins on.
Place in a medium to large saucepan and cover with salted water.
Cook about 25 minutes, until they can be pierced easily with a fork; drain. Leaving the potatoes in a hot saucepan, drop in the chopped parsley and the margarine.
Stir well until the potatoes are coated.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and serve hot with steamed green beans or any kind of meat dish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil.
Cook until tender.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch in a small amount of water.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Make jello and chill a little.
Fold pineapple, bananas and marshmallows into jello.
Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Cook pineapple juice, sugar, flour and egg until thick; cool.
Beat in cream cheese.
Chill for 1 hour.
Add Cool Whip. Spread over jello and let stand 1 hour before serving.

title: dog biscuits
directions: In a large bowl pour hot water over oatmeal, margarine and bouillon; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in powdered milk, cornmeal and egg.
Add flour 1/2 cup at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Knead 3 to 4 minutes adding more flour if necessary to make a stiff dough.
Pat or roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut with favorite cookie cutter.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Allow to cool and dry out until hard.
Makes approximately 1 3/4 pounds.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and line with bread.
Cover with layers of chicken, mushrooms, pimento and water chestnuts.
Mix together soups and mayonnaise and pour over casserole.
Mix eggs and milk.
Pour over soup mixture.
Cover with sliced cheese. Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute ingredients until tender.
Mix with cream of chicken soup and 2 cups of milk.
Keep on low or medium heat for about 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with Ritz crackers or rolls.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Toss berries with sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and lemon juice. Place in large baking casserole.
Dot with butter.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add salt and pepper, broth, water and milk.
Bring to a hard boil.
Add egg noodles.
Cook until half done.
Add broccoli and cook 5 minutes or until tender. Cut cheese up in small chunks.
Add to soup mixture until melted. Add half and half.
I like to add bits of chicken to make a hearty chicken soup.

title: mom's pasta salad
directions: Pre-cook and cool pasta and frozen vegetables.
Drain peas. Mix and add dressing.

title: ranchero dip
directions: Cook beef and drain off juice.
Add beans and salsa.
Stir and let simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add (grated) cheese.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Put Ranchero Dip in a crock-Pot on low to keep it hot.

title: a good salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine milk and lemon juice.
Beat until mixed well.
Add Cool Whip, bananas, marshmallows and pineapple. Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: bonnie's shrimp dip
directions: Mix first three ingredients. For bottom layer, smooth onto large plate; thin layer cocktail sauce, shrimp, olives and sprinkle cheese on top. Enjoy with chips.

title: raspberry almond shortbread thumbprints
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large mixer bowl, combine sugar, butter and almond extract. Beat at medium speed until creamy (2 to 3 minutes). Cover and chill dough at least 1 hour. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheets. With thumb, make indentation in center of each ball (edges may crack slightly). Fill each indentation with about 1/4 teaspoon jam. Bake for 14 to 18 minutes or until edges are very lightly browned. Let stand 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet. Cool completely. Drizzle cookies with glaze.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 9x13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: basic white sauce(microwave)
directions: To melt butter in a 1-quart glass bowl or casserole, microwave on High for 30 seconds.
Stir in flour and salt to make a smooth paste.
Blend in milk gradually.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Yields 1 cup creamy white sauce (thin).

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Trim and wash broccoli thoroughly; cut flowerets and stems into bite-size pieces.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add melted chocolate, vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat for 5 minutes after each egg.
Pour into a previously baked pie shell. Top with 1/2 pint whipping cream, whipped with sugar to taste. Sprinkle with little grated chocolate.
