Chill overnight or at least 3 hours in fridge.

title: jeffrey's favorite marinated pork
directions: Trim tenderloin, place in a glass baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over meat.
Marinate overnight.
Remove from marinade, boil marinade 3 to 5 minutes; cool.
Bake meat at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until done.
Remove meat from pan and let cool.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices and arrange in a small dish. Pour marinade over and toss.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours before serving.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Beat eggs until lemon colored and blend dry ingredients.
Add melted butter and milk; blend well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Allow to set before serving.

title: kourafedes(wedding cookies)
directions: Have butter at room temperature.
Beat until creamy.
Add sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Mix in baking powder and flour to form soft dough.
Add nuts, if desired.
Roll out dough
and cut with cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 minutes.
(Temperature depends on your oven.)
While cookies are still hot, roll in confectioners sugar until cooled.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: tomato salad
directions: Arrange tomato slices in slightly overlapping circles on a deep round plate or platter.
For dressing, mix oil, vinegar, basil, garlic, salt and a few grinds of pepper; pour over tomatoes.
Combine scallions and parsley; sprinkle evenly on top.

title: pineapple cheese cake pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Then add crushed pineapple. Mix well and pour into graham cracker pie shells.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 or 3 hours or overnight.
Then serve.
You can freeze this pie.

title: chocolate macadamia chews
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs and vanilla. In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; blend into creamed mixture. Blend in nuts and coconut. Stir in M&M's bits. Drop by heaping teaspoon 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten slightly with back of spoon. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set. Don't overbake. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Cool completely on wire rack. Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Fry chicken until done; cool.
Saute
celery, onion and garlic until tender.
Add soup and milk.
Simmer
until all is mixed well.
Add chicken that has been deboned
and
cut	up. Add
about 8	to 16 ounces cooked spaghetti and
cups cheese.
Mix well.
Put in oven and bake 45 minutes.
May have to add more milk.
The last few minutes, sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.

title: bohemian bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Mix milk, sugar, salt, shortening and lemon rind.
Stir until shortening is well mixed.
Stir in egg.
Add raisins and nuts.
Add 1 1/4 cups flour and mix well.
Add rest of flour and knead until smooth.
Put in bowl and rise double.
Punch down and let rise again for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter and chips; cool.
Stir in oats, flour and brown sugar.
Press firmly into bottom and about 1 inch up sides of pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean peppers; cook until slightly soft.
Remove from pan; drain off water.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix jello, boiling water, 7-Up and pineapple together. Set aside. Combine egg, sugar, juice and flour and cook until thick. After mixture is cooled, fold into jello mixture. Add mini marshmallows and allow to set up. Spread Cool Whip on top and garnish with pecans.

title: cherry pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish. Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour, salt and baking powder. Pour over butter. Heat cherries, 1 cup sugar, 1 cup hot water and Jell-O. Pour over batter. Bake at 375°.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In skillet over medium high heat, put 1 tablespoon oil.
When oil gets hot, put in half of the chicken; cook until brown and remove.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Over medium heat, add remaining 1 tablespoon oil; when hot, stir-fry vegetables with ginger and garlic powder until tender and crisp.
Add soup, soy and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet and heat. Serve over rice.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Combine cream cheese and oleo; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Add flour; mix well.
Shape dough into 32 balls.
Chill.
Place in miniature (1-3/4-inch) muffin pans, shaping each ball into a tart shell.
Set aside. Combine egg, oleo, vanilla, brown sugar and pecans.
Spoon mixture into tart shells, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugars, eggs, pineapple and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Combine dry ingredients, then add to first mixture.
Add nuts; mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto oiled cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Yields 6 dozen cookies.
Store in loosely covered container.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, oil and flavorings.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Grease bottom of a glass with oil.
Dip in white sugar.
Press top of cookie.
Do this in sugar for each cookie.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Watch closely.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a bowl. Pat in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.

title: spicy zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs with sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat in the dry ingredients.
Add zucchini, raisins and nuts.
Bake in two loaf pans at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: homestyle vegetable soup
directions: In a large stockpot, add tomato juice, peeled tomatoes and fatback.
Bring to a boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add cabbage and okra.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add lima beans and potatoes.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 two cup servings.

title: scallops and pea pods
directions: Thaw scallops and drain well.
Cut large scallops in half. Run warm water over frozen pea pods to thaw; drain well.
Cut onion into slices and cherry tomatoes in half lengthwise; set aside.
In small bowl, stir together sherry, water, cornstarch, bouillon granules, sugar, soy sauce and ginger; set aside.

title: shrimp-crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Blend with mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Place pork chops into a 9 x 13 pan with 1 c. of water.
Place in oven on 350°.
Cook stuffing mix according to directions on package.
Once done, take the pork chops out of the oven and salt and pepper.
Place stuffing on top of pork chops and cover pan with foil.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until done.

title: roast venison(recipe from 1913 parents and relatives)
directions: Choose leg or saddle.
Makes enough for family of 4.
Allow 1/2 pound of meat per person.
Season with garlic, pepper and salt.
Rub meat with flour.
Place on rack in open roasting pan. Roast for 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 325° and cook 30 minutes per pound.
If layer of fat is thin, place several bacon strips on top.
May use this recipe for elk or beef also.
If venison flavor is too strong, flavor may be improved by standing for 1 hour in a mixture of olive oil and lemon juice or use French dressing.

title: cheese and beef casserole
directions: Prepare shells and cheese dinner as on package.
Add tomatoes and mix.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and onion. Spoon dinner mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with meat mixture.
Sprinkle with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the sugars, butter and peanut butter.
Add eggs, soda and corn syrup.
Continue mixing thoroughly.
Stir in by hand, mixing the oatmeal, 3 cups at a time, with the chocolate chips and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheets. Bake in 350° oven until done and lightly brown.
Makes a large batch, using no flour.

title: orange-glazed sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, salt and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients; mix.
Drop by tablespoons.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Spread "Orange Glaze" on warm cookies.

title: tangy asparagus linguini
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat in large skillet.
Cook and stir onion and garlic until onion is soft.
Add asparagus.
Cook and stir for an additional 2 minutes.
Add wine and lemon juice; cook an additional minute.
Season with pepper to taste.
Remove from heat.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Line bottom of 8 x 13 pan with bread.
Mix ham, mayonnaise, onion and celery.
Spread over the bread and cover with another layer of bread.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Add cold water.
Cook 1/2 hour; drain pot.
In baking dish, add ingredients.
Cover with boiling water.
Bake 4 hours.

title: oatmeal honey bread
directions: Mix together quick oatmeal and 1 cup water in microwave for 3 1/2 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm.
Put 2 cups warm water and dry yeast together in a large bowl and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar. Let begin to work.
Add oat mixture, honey, salt, oil and flour to yeast mixture.
Mix well and knead on floured board until smooth and elastic.
Place in a bowl, greased well with Puritan oil.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Punch down and roll over; let rise again.
Punch down and form into 2 or 3 loaves, depending on pan size.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Can be made into buns also.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together corn meal, flour and salt into large bowl.
Mix onion.
Stir in milk.
Then stir in egg.
(Dough will be soft.) Let mixture stand about 3 minutes.
Drop from teaspoon a few at a time in deep fryer.
Takes about 3 minutes for each puppy to brown.

title: low-fat seafood with angel hair pasta
directions: Heat olive oil in a large nonstick pan.
Put water on to boil for pasta.
Add garlic and tomatoes to olive oil and saute, stirring occasionally, for about 5 minutes.
Add wine, seafood and basil or parsley and bring to a boil and then immediately turn heat to low.
Add pasta to boiling water.
Simmer seafood mixture for about 7 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add cooked pasta to seafood mixture.
Sprinkle with additional parsley or basil and Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.
About 6 grams of fat per serving.

title: nanny's homemade bread
directions: Mix yeast, warm water and 1/2 cup sugar in a small bowl.
In another bowl, add salt, 1 cup sugar, instant potatoes and cold water to make a thin mixture.
In a large bowl, take flour and blend in shortening well.
Add both liquid mixtures to flour.
Let rise to double size.
Work down using liquid shortening to keep hands wet.
Pinch off balls about 2-inches in diameter to make rolls or divide out in bread pans to make loaves.
Put in greased pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes or until brown.
Brush on melted butter immediately.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat iron skillet or bread pan with bacon drippings (or oil) in 400° oven.
Pour in batter and bake until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salsa together. Sprinkle black olives, lettuce and cheese on top. Dip chips and enjoy.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until done; drain off water.
Let cool; peel.
Blend and cream potatoes with mixer.
Add sugar, margarine and eggs.
Then add milk and seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells (2 or 3 depends on how thick you prefer pie). Bake 30 to 40 minutes until crust is golden brown in preheated oven at 325°.

title: candied pecan halves
directions: Combine sugar, water, cinnamon and salt in pan.
Cook to 236°. Remove from heat and add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and mix.
Add warm nuts.
Turn over and stir until all nuts are coated.
Turn out on cookie sheet and separate nuts with fork.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix butter, cheese and Worcestershire well; add flour, salt and cayenne pepper.
Mix well; add Rice Krispies and blend.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Mix Jell-O, water, pineapple juice and sugar.
Partly set. Whip until foamy.
Whip condensed milk until stiff.
Combine the 2 mixture in a very large bowl; blend until well mixed.
Add can of drained, crushed pineapple.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: herbed chicken and vegetable kabobs
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large, self-closing plastic bag or glass dish.
Cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Add to marinade; toss to coat.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade; discard marinade.
Spear chicken and vegetables on metal skewers.
Lightly sprinkle chicken and vegetables with Grill-Mates seasonings.
Preheat grill or broiler.
Grill skewers 10 to 15 minutes, turning frequently.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemonade
directions: Dissolve sugar in water over low heat and bring to a boil. Simmer 5 minutes.
Cool completely.
Add lemon juice; cover and refrigerate.
Let set for several hours.
Strain.
When ready to serve, add ice, club soda and 7-Up or Sprite.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Boil potato until well done; cream with butter.
Work all sugar into potato to form stiff dough; roll 1/4 inch thick. Spread with thin layer of peanut butter; form into roll.
Place in refrigerator until mixture sets; slice in small pieces.
Coconut or chopped nuts may be substituted for peanut butter.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Sift together dry ingredients. Add vanilla to oleo mixture. Add dry ingredients and milk alternately, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: banana bran bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add egg, mix thoroughly.
Add banana, vanilla, salt and soda.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, nuts and bran.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: beef-rice skillet(heart healthy)
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in 10-inch skillet.
Add bouillon, dry mustard, rice and water.
Simmer about 25 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Stir in green pepper and tomato.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover, turn off heat and let stand 2 to 3 minutes. Instead of ground beef, turkey burger may be used.
Quick and easy!

title: never fail frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in double boiler.
Beat constantly over boiling water for 4 minutes.
Frost cake immediately.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook beef and onions; drain. Simmer other ingredients while beef cooks. Mix all together and simmer. Add a little water if needed. Cook for 30 minutes. Serve with sour cream, corn chips and cheese or Mexican cornbread. Serves 6 (1 1/2 cups).

title: black walnut layer cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and brown sugar. Mix well, then add white sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together and alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and nuts. Bake at 325° until done.

title: banana fudge pie
directions: Prepare crust according to directions for filled one pie crust.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: chess cake or caramel brownies
directions: Melt brown sugar and butter together.
Add white sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and vanilla.
Stir well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan about 30 minutes at 350°.
When slightly cool, cut in squares.
Can be rolled in powdered sugar.

title: cardamom sour cream bread
directions: Cream butter and
sugar;
beat	in eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and cardamom, stir half in batter. Add
sour cream and vanilla; add rest of flour mixture.
Pour into
greased pan.
Rap	pan
on table to remove air pockets. Bake
at
350° for
50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and chill.
Serve cold.

title: gretta's chili con carne
directions: In heavy skillet, cook meat, onion and green pepper until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf. Serves 4 hearty appetites!

title: three flavored pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating one minute after each addition.
Add flavorings.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Begin and end with dry ingredients.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for one hour and 15 minutes.
Apply glaze on warm cake.

title: christmas flowers(from 1975 edition)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add yolks and chocolate; add flour mixture alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Beat vigorously and fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake in cupcake tins. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes or until done.

title: pot roast
directions: Place pot roast on a piece of aluminum foil (heavy duty) large enough to completely seal the roast; sprinkle dry onion mix on top; wrap aluminum foil snugly around the roast and seal firmly; place in pan; bake at 300° for 3 hours or 200° for 9 hours.

title: tandoori chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate for 6-24 hours.
Bake covered at 400°F for a half hour.
Bake uncovered another half hour.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and salt.
Add 1 cup flour at a time until all flour is mixed in; when adding third cup, mix in by hand. (You may not need all of third cup.)
Put in ungreased round cake pan.
Press firmly in pan with spoon.
Smooth down.
Take thumb and press around outside to create thumbprint.
Prick top with fork. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: tomato and chickpea stew
directions: In heavy bottomed saucepan or casserole, heat olive oil and add onion and garlic. Saute until onion is tender and add paprika. Stir a minute.
Add tomatoes, bay leaf and tomato paste. Simmer together over medium heat 10 minutes.
Add potatoes, thyme, oregano, broth from beans, chickpeas and salt to taste.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir from time to time.
Add plenty of ground pepper and adjust seasonings. Serve. Serves 6.

title: updated beef stroganoff
directions: Cook the pasta according to package directions; drain and keep warm.
Coat a large skillet with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium heat.
Cook and stir beef, half at a time, for 1 to 2 minutes or until browned.
Season with pepper.
Remove and keep warm.
In the same skillet, saute mushrooms and onion in oil until tender.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add broth, stirring until blended.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Return beef to skillet and heat through.
Serve over pasta.
Top with green onions and sour cream.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Cook noodles; drain and separate.

title: portuguese sopa transmontana(soup from beyond the mountains)
directions: Put the water, roughly chopped vegetables, salt and pork in large saucepan.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Dice toasted bread and when serving soup, add this and the butter to soup.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked crust.
Bake at 250° until done.
Make meringue with egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Brown meringue.

title: sunday best chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken parts with all seasonings and cheese to taste.
Dot with butter and bake, covered with foil, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: zenobia bryant's applesauce cake
directions: Cream applesauce,
butter
and	sugar
together and put into boiling
water
with
1 teaspoon soda.
Mix raisins, nuts and spices with
flour	and
stir
into first mixture.	Can be baked in layers or loaf.	Cook at 350° until done.

title: world's best chuck roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place meat in roasting pan lined with aluminum foil.
Brush meat with steak sauce.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over the meat. Spread with mushroom soup.
Wrap loosely in foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix all together and make in roll.
Chill overnight.
Slice and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or brown in 350° oven.

title: old-fashioned nut cake
directions: Lightly grease a 10-inch tube pan with solid vegetable shortening.
Pan should be 4 1/2 inches deep and a single unit pan (not with a removable bottom).
Line the pan bottom with wax paper and cut to fit.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; then set aside.
Combine milk and rum; set aside.
Preheat oven to 275°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Add garlic and seasoning. Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry-sour cream corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease twelve medium-sized muffin cups or line with paper liners; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients in medium bowl.
Add combined egg, sour cream and apple juice concentrate; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Gently stir in blueberries.
Spoon batter into prepared cups, filling each cup 3/4 full.

title: irish soda bread
directions: About an hour before serving or a day ahead:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
In a large bowl, mix the first 6 ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in raisins.
In cup, beat egg whites slightly. Remove 1 tablespoon of egg whites and reserve.
Stir buttermilk and remaining egg whites into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Turn dough onto floured surface and with well floured hands, knead dough 8 to 10 strokes.
Shake dough into ball and place in casserole.
In center of dough, cut a 4-inch cross 1/4 inch deep.
Brush dough with egg whites.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool bread in casserole dish for 10 minutes.
Remove from dish and serve.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: coconut delight
directions: Layer as directed.
Crumble flour and oleo together on bottom of dish or pan.
Put pecans (ground up) on top of mixture.
Cook for 20 minutes or until light brown; cool.
Mix up cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Put on top of pecans (will be hard to spread).
Put Cool Whip on top of this.
Sprinkle coconut.
Mix pudding with milk and coconut flavoring until firm.
Put on top of rest.
Add more Cool Whip and sprinkle more coconut on top.

title: creamy potato chowder soup
directions: Dice potatoes and slice the onions.
Cook the potatoes and onions in a small amount of water until tender and then rub through a sieve.
Add the mushroom soup, butter, milk, salt and pepper to taste, nutmeg and mustard.
Heat gently.
For color, a few green peas, sliced carrot or chopped pepper may be added.
Serve hot or icy cold.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread over chicken, beef or pork for roasting or grilling.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers 1/2 inch thick.
Cut out center to form ring.
Add 1 cup lime to 1 gallon of water.
Soak cucumbers overnight in solution (only use enamel or crock-type bowl).

title: orange jello
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add 6 ounce can orange juice and 1 cup juice from drained pineapple and oranges.
Add fruit and set.
Top with lemon instant pudding.
Can top pudding with grated cheese.

title: quick pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix altogether (around 2 minutes).
Pour into pie pan.
Chill at least 3 hours, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: villa montana salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or food processor until smooth. Store in refrigerator in a covered container until ready to use. Also makes a great marinade for chicken.

title: pecan pie surprise bars
directions: Set aside 2/3 cup of cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, butter and 1 egg in a large mixing bowl.
Mix with a fork until crumbly.
Press crumbs in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix together until crumb like.
Press mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: "chicken" pot pie
directions: Cook vegetables.
In large pan add Fri-chick, vegetables and water.
In glass mix seasonings and cornstarch with a little water until smooth.
Add mixture to pan and thicken.
Put 2 pie shells in a preheated oven at 350°.
When very light golden add filling mix from pan.
Take other thawed shells, place upside down on pie. Press edges together.
Bake until top is golden brown.

title: dirt
directions: Grind cookies real fine; set aside.
Mix pudding with milk. Add cream cheese; mix thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly. Layer cookie crumbs, then pudding mix alternately, finishing with crumbs.

title: smoky barbecue sauce
directions: Saute garlic in oleo.
In heavy pan add garlic and oleo to rest of the ingredients.
Simmer 25 minutes on low to medium heat, stirring frequently.
This can be stored in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 5 cups.

title: hawaiian nut bread
directions: Using a large mixing bowl, combine the dry ingredients.
Add the nuts and set aside.
Combine the remaining ingredients and add these to the dry mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Pour the batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, pumpkin, oil and eggs in a bowl.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts and 1/4 cup water.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour 15 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: prairie fruitcake
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients. Mix in applesauce. Add baking soda, salt and spices. Blend in flour and water. Add remaining ingredients. Sprinkle brown sugar on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in a 2 or 2 1/2-quart, buttered casserole.
Add chicken pieces.
Blend soups with mayonnaise and lemon juice. Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Sprinkle bread crumbs over cheese, then dribble butter over bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quick veggie soup
directions: Combine vegetables, soup mix and juice in a Dutch oven; bring to boil.
Cook ground beef in a skillet until beef is browned; crumble, then drain off fat.
Stir meat into vegetables; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: peach delight
directions: Beat egg whites. Add cream of tartar and slowly add sugar. Add crushed cracker crumbs and nuts to egg white mixture. Put in cake pan (preferably sheet cake pan). Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes. Cool. Cover with whipped topping and top with peach or any kind of pie filling. Should stand over night or several hours. Cut in squares and serve.

title: new england crock-pot beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in crock-pot turned on low.
Check beans in morning by blowing on beans in spoon; if outer coating curls back, they are ready to prepare.
Be sure beans are soft before mixing.
Drain beans over large container to keep the liquid.
Mix all remaining ingredients except salt pork.
(I mix these the night before and refrigerate.)
Cut salt pork in 1/2-inch slices and score to the rind.
Place 3 or 4 pieces of salt pork in bottom of crock-pot, then a layer of beans, some of mix.
Alternate until full.
Reserve 1 cup liquid to add during cooking.
Cook on high for 6 hours; remove to baking dish, picking out salt pork pieces to put on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crock-pot italian beef
directions: Cook on high overnight (8 to 10 hours) and on low for 10 hours.
Remove fat, as needed.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
except
corn.
Add	corn by folding in	last.
Drop
from tablespoon into hot fat and cook until brown and crisp. Drain on paper towels.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, butter, green onions and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Gently stir in potatoes, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into a lightly buttered 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese and the crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all but last two ingredients together and pour into a baking dish.
Melt butter.
Pour crackers into melted butter and mix well.
Spread crackers on top of vegetable, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Keep stored in a tightly sealed container.
Use 3 to 4 tablespoons in a mug of hot water.
Great cold weather drink!

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and 1 tablespoon water. Add flour and mix well.
Add nuts.
Form small rolls about 1 1/2 inches.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven (300°) for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
While hot, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: christmas fruitcake
directions: Combine nuts, dates and cherries.
Set aside.

title: boy scout stew
directions: Cook carrots.
Saute the onion. Add to carrots.
Cut ground beef into chunks of meat.
Brown and pour off grease.
Add cooked carrots and uncooked diced potatoes and small amount of water. Simmer until potatoes are done. Add soup and soy sauce.
Heat until stew is hot and serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Note:
Can be made ahead except for dressing and taco chips. Add these 3 items just before serving.

title: orange carrots
directions: Heat orange juice and marshmallows together until marshmallows are melted.
Add carrots and heat until hot.
Top in serving dish with nuts, as desired.

title: stephanie's chicken noodles
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Dissolve chicken gravy mix in hot water.
Tear up chicken in the chicken broth and add the gravy mixture.
Then add the bag of noodles.
Cook 15 minutes until done and serve.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tortellini chicken and artichoke salad
directions: Cook green beans according to package; drain.
Meanwhile, cook tortellini to desired doneness as directed on package; rinse with cold water.

title: carol's cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix first three ingredients. Press in a 10 inch spring form pan. Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time beating well after each addition. Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Remove from oven and let stand for 15 minutes. Increase oven temperature to 450°. Mix together the sour cream, 1/4 c. sugar and vanilla.
Spread over top of cheesecake and bake ten more minutes.
Cool and refrigerate overnight.

title: ham salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: venison meat balls
directions: Put meat, cheese, seasoning and eggs in a bowl. Wet the slices of bread, squeeze dry and shred into bowl.
Mix ingredients. Form into meat balls. Roll in bread crumbs.
Cook in oil until browned. Drop meat balls in boiling pasta sauce. Simmer about 10 minutes. Serve over rice or pasta.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add pumpkin to creamed mixture.
Add all other ingredients in order given.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Refrigerate dough overnight.
Roll very thin.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip. Break cake into medium size pieces.
Toss lightly.
Pour into large bowl.

title: chicken fettucini alfredo
directions: Heat
oil
in
skillet; add onions, garlic and chicken. Saute until
chicken
is brown.
Stir in cream, alfredo sauce mix, mushrooms,
tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat
to medium and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in parsley and
basil. Remove
from
heat.
Toss
with
cooked pasta and serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: hearty chicken-rice soup
directions: Combine chicken and water in Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and save broth.
Let chicken cool, then skin and bone.
Chop coarsely; set aside.
Remove and discard fat from broth.
(Do this the day before serving.)
Add rice and remaining ingredients to boiling broth. Cover and cook 20 minutes or until rice and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in chicken; cook until thoroughly heated.
Yields about 9 cups.

title: blackberry sparkle salad
directions: Prepare gelatin as directed on package.
Stir in bananas, nuts, drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Combine beans and taco seasoning mix.
Spread this mixture in an oblong shallow dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: imitation whipped cream frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 15 minutes.
Use cubed margarine, not soft or whipped.

title: yummy chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda and salt.
In saucepan combine butter, water and cocoa, stirring constantly.
Bring to rolling boil over low heat.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing well. Stir in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into greased pan and bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: potato puff
directions: Make instant potatoes as directed.
Mix all together.
Dot butter on top.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 casseroles.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries, reserving liquid in saucepan. Sprinkle jello and let stand 1 minute. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until jello dissolves. Remove from heat and add cream cheese, stirring until smooth. Stir in fruit, cola beverage and pecans. Pour into lightly oiled 4-cup mold. Cover and chill.

title: creamy cabbage
directions: Wash and chop cabbage.
In large saucepan, bring the 1/2 cup water to a boil.
Add 1 tablespoon of butter, salt, pepper and cabbage.
Steam for about 20 minutes and pour the can of cream of chicken soup over onto cabbage.
Cook on low for 6 minutes. Serve with favorite meat dish.

title: shells with clam sauce
directions: Prepare the shells according to directions on package.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes; remove stem ends.
Cut crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Combine meal, salt and pepper; coat tomato slices with meal mixture.
Brown in shortening on one side; turn.
Reduce heat; cook until slices are brown on both sides.
Serve hot. Yield:
4 to 5 servings.

title: crocheted doilies
directions: For each sandwich use two slices of white bread lightly buttered.
On one piece place thin slices of ham and Monterey Jack cheese.
Top with second piece.
Carefully dip into mixture of beaten egg and milk (1 egg to 1/3 cup milk and 1/4 teaspoon salt per sandwich).
Fry in mixture of 2 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons oil until brown on both sides.
Cool 5 minutes, then cut into triangles and serve with avocado wedges and alfalfa sprouts sprinkled with lemon juice.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix thoroughly and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yield:
3 pies.

title: e-z cream of broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
Add mushroom soup and 1 can of water or milk.
Stir in sour cream (may add more, if desired). Heat until hot enough to serve.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and cold water.
Boil until brittle when you try it in cold water.
Then pour slowly over the stiffly beaten whites of 2 eggs.
Add cream of tartar, vanilla to taste and nuts when it is nearly ready to pour.
Mark into squares.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice on bottom with salt, pepper and onion.
Mix celery and mushroom soups with water.
Pour over rice.
Place chicken on rice.
Spoon onion soup over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll biscuits in sugar/cinnamon mixture or shake in zip-top bag to coat.
Drop coated biscuit pieces in Bundt pan.
Melt butter or margarine.
Add remaining sugar mixture and bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
If desired, mix chopped pecans with sugar/cinnamon before rolling biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately, inverting onto waxed paper. It may not absorb all the butter during baking, so it could be a little messy.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat sugar and softened cream cheese until smooth.
Add thawed strawberries, then fold in bananas.
Add pecans (if desired), pineapple and Cool Whip.
Pour in muffin tins and freeze.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place Tater Tots on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over Tater Tots.
Spread grated cheese, then corn flakes.
Pour melted butter over.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: frypan vegetables
directions: Into skillet put all ingredients.
Cook on moderate heat until tender-crisp.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; mix with other ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Add toppings as desired when served: lettuce (cut small), grated Mozzarella or Cheddar cheese, sour cream, taco chips.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Add cut up onion, tomato sauce and tomato paste; bring to a boil.
Add seasoning and reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Boil lasagna noodles and drain. Take meat mixture off heat and stir in cottage cheese.
Put a layer of noodles in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, half the sauce, half of each of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted on top.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 475° for 1 hour.
Cut in half and scrape out insides.
Mix potatoes with margarine, chopped onion, green onion tops or green pepper and canned milk.
Put back into shells and top with grated cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: polish sausage and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
Fry sausage until browned.
Remove. Drain all but 2 tablespoons fat in skillet.
Add onion and pepper. Saute until tender.
Add soup, water and seasonings.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add sausage and noodles.
Pour into greased casserole. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: smoky brisket
directions: Place brisket, fat side up, on large sheet of heavy-duty foil. Add liquid smoke and sprinkle salt on top.
Wrap brisket in foil and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Drain marinade.
Spread Worcestershire sauce on top of brisket just before baking.
Seal foil tightly to prevent leaking of juices.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: scandinavian fruit soup
directions: Dice first 3 ingredients and cover in large pot with 10 cups of water and stand 30 minutes.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; stir and scrape bottom.
Simmer, stirring 10 minutes. Add currants, raisins and salt and allow to cool.
To thin, dilute with apple juice and serve garnished with sour cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces (wings, back and neck are delicious for soup).
Place chicken in cooker with water, salt, celery, carrot and onion.
Cook slowly until chicken leaves the bone.
Thicken with 1 tablespoon flour mixed smoothly in three tablespoons water or serve thin.
If too much cooking absorbs, add a cup or more hot water.

title: macaroni shells salad
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown sausage in a pan until crumbly; drain well.
Unroll crescent roll dough; press into a pizza pan to form crust.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese. Combine milk and eggs in a bowl; mix well.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy hash brown potatoes
directions: Place frozen potatoes in dish.
Melt everything else in double boiler or microwave.
Mix with potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Slice and cook carrots until tender.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients and pour over carrots.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight or longer.

title: george jones' chicken breast veggies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven; mix well.
Add enough water to cover.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with hot cornbread.

title: moon over miami
directions: This is not a recipe for your "best company," but my Great Uncle Milton loved it and so do kids.

title: chocolate eclair squares
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix the 2 packages of vanilla pudding with 3 1/2 cups milk.
Stir in the Cool Whip topping.
Spread half of the pudding mixture on top of the graham crackers.
Place another layer of graham crackers on top of the pudding.
Spread the second half of the pudding over the second layer of graham crackers.
Top with a third layer of graham crackers.
Frost with any chocolate frosting or the one listed below.
Prepare one to two days in advance and store in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well with each egg. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.	Mix well.
Fold in extracts.

title: ireland's happy apple cake
directions: With mixer, beat butter and sugar until creamy. Add eggs, one at a time. Add Irish whiskey. Stir in lemon zest and diced apples. Sift together dry ingredients.
Fold into butter mixture. Blend well.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until tested done in middle.
Cut into 9 squares.
Serve warm or cooled with pistachio or vanilla ice cream.

title: cheddar baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes about 1 hour (don't wrap in foil).
Cut hot potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out, saving shells.

title: mama's biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in enough milk to make soft dough. Knead lightly about 1/2 minute.
Pat or roll out 1/2-inch thick. Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemonade frozen dessert
directions: Mix crackers, powdered sugar and margarine.
Put in 2 pie tins or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save some crumbs for the top.
Mix lemonade and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put on top of crumbs in pan.
Add crumbs on top.
Freeze.
Keeps well.
